{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01CsVRDLvL6pm6iru4Cs5mLy","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now let me create a comprehensive summary document of my findings.\n\n## Summary of Cloche Codebase Exploration\n\nI've completed a thorough exploration of the Cloche codebase. Here are my findings for the four key areas you requested:\n\n### 1. **Web UI Structure - Run Details Page**\n\n**Template Location:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/run_detail.html`\n\nThe Run Details page is structured as follows:\n- **Main Template Block:** `{{define \"content\"}}` (lines 1-72)\n- **Layout:** Inherits from `layout.html` which provides HTML structure with navbar and main container\n- **Dynamic Elements:**\n  - Run metadata section (title, workflow, state badge, container status, error message)\n  - Steps table with accordion-style expandable output rows\n  - Live log viewer with SSE (Server-Sent Events) streaming\n\n**Key Features:**\n- Real-time log streaming from `/api/runs/{id}/stream` SSE endpoint\n- Polling-based step status updates (every 2 seconds for active runs)\n- Container status monitoring with \"Delete Container\" button for completed runs\n- Step output viewer with lazy-loading when rows are expanded\n- Auto-scroll toggle in log viewer\n\n**Handler Code:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (lines 363-390)\n- `handleRunDetail()` - serves HTML page\n- `handleAPIRunDetail()` - serves JSON API response\n\n### 2. **'cloche stop' Command Implementation**\n\n**CLI Command Flow:**\n1. **User Entry Point:** `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go` (lines 67-68)\n   - Routes `\"stop\"` subcommand to `cmdStop()`\n\n2. **CLI Handler:** `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go` (lines 395-407)\n   ```go\n   func cmdStop(ctx context.Context, client pb.ClocheServiceClient, args []string) {\n       if len(args) < 1 {\n           fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"usage: cloche stop <run-id>\\n\")\n           os.Exit(1)\n       }\n       _, err := client.StopRun(ctx, &pb.StopRunRequest{RunId: args[0]})\n       if err != nil {\n           fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"error: %v\\n\", err)\n           os.Exit(1)\n       }\n       fmt.Printf(\"Stopped run: %s\\n\", args[0])\n   }\n   ```\n\n3. **gRPC Service Definition:** `/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto` (lines 11, 72-76)\n   ```proto\n   rpc StopRun(StopRunRequest) returns (StopRunResponse);\n   \n   message StopRunRequest {\n     string run_id = 1;\n   }\n   \n   message StopRunResponse {}\n   ```\n\n4. **Daemon Handler:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` (lines 616-637)\n   ```go\n   func (s *ClocheServer) StopRun(ctx context.Context, req *pb.StopRunRequest) (*pb.StopRunResponse, error) {\n       s.mu.Lock()\n       containerID, ok := s.runIDs[req.RunId]\n       s.mu.Unlock()\n       \n       if !ok {\n           return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"run %q not found or already completed\", req.RunId)\n       }\n       \n       if err := s.container.Stop(ctx, containerID); err != nil {\n           return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"stopping run: %w\", err)\n       }\n       \n       // Mark as cancelled in store\n       run, err := s.store.GetRun(ctx, req.RunId)\n       if err == nil {\n           run.Complete(domain.RunStateCancelled)\n           _ = s.store.UpdateRun(ctx, run)\n       }\n       \n       return &pb.StopRunResponse{}, nil\n   }\n   ```\n\n**Key Points:**\n- Looks up container ID in `runIDs` map (only contains active runs)\n- Calls `container.Stop()` to stop the Docker container\n- Updates run state to `RunStateCancelled` in the database\n\n### 3. **Run State Machine**\n\n**State Type Definition:** `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go` (lines 8-16)\n```go\ntype RunState string\n\nconst (\n    RunStatePending   RunState = \"pending\"\n    RunStateRunning   RunState = \"running\"\n    RunStateSucceeded RunState = \"succeeded\"\n    RunStateFailed    RunState = \"failed\"\n    RunStateCancelled RunState = \"cancelled\"\n)\n```\n\n**State Transitions:**\n\n| From | To | Trigger | Location |\n|------|-----|---------|----------|\n| Pending | Running | `run.Start()` (on container launch) | `grpc/server.go:178` |\n| Running | Succeeded | `run.Complete(RunStateSucceeded)` (on exit code 0) | `grpc/server.go:318` |\n| Running | Failed | `run.Fail(msg)` (on non-zero exit) | `grpc/server.go:324` |\n| Running | Cancelled | `run.Complete(RunStateCancelled)` (via StopRun) | `grpc/server.go:632` |\n\n**Terminal vs Active States:**\n- **Terminal States:** `succeeded`, `failed`, `cancelled` (run is complete)\n- **Active States:** `pending`, `running` (run is ongoing)\n\n**Terminal State Detection Logic:**\n- Web UI: Lines 125-128 in `run_detail.html` and 692-694 in `handler.go`\n- CLI Poll: `/workspace/cmd/cloche/poll.go` (lines 54-63)\n  ```go\n  switch resp.State {\n  case \"succeeded\":\n      os.Exit(0)\n  case \"failed\", \"cancelled\":\n      if resp.ErrorMessage != \"\" {\n          fmt.Fprintf(os.Stderr, \"Error: %s\\n\", resp.ErrorMessage)\n      }\n      os.Exit(1)\n  }\n  ```\n- Host Executor: `/workspace/internal/host/executor.go` (lines 190-193)\n  ```go\n  switch run.State {\n  case domain.RunStateSucceeded, domain.RunStateFailed, domain.RunStateCancelled:\n      return run.State, nil\n  }\n  ```\n\n### 4. **Web Server Route Definitions**\n\n**Server Setup:** `/workspace/cmd/cloched/main.go` (lines 85-103)\n- HTTP server initialized with `web.NewHandler()`\n- Listens on address from `CLOCHE_HTTP` env var or config (defaults not set if empty)\n- Routes defined in the handler's ServeMux\n\n**Route Table:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (lines 121-136)\n\n| Method | Pattern | Handler Function | Purpose |\n|--------|---------|------------------|---------|\n| GET | `/{$}` | `handleProjectOverview()` | Dashboard - projects with health |\n| GET | `/projects/{name}/runs` | `handleProjectRuns()` | Redirects to `/runs?project=...` |\n| GET | `/runs` | `handleRunsList()` | All runs with project filter |\n| GET | `/runs/{id}` | `handleRunDetail()` | Single run detail page |\n| GET | `/projects/{name}` | `handleProjectDetail()` | Project detail with workflows |\n| GET | `/api/projects` | `handleAPIProjects()` | JSON: projects with health |\n| GET | `/api/runs` | `handleAPIRuns()` | JSON: all runs list |\n| GET | `/api/runs/{id}` | `handleAPIRunDetail()` | JSON: run detail |\n| GET | `/api/runs/{id}/steps/{step}/output` | `handleAPIStepOutput()` | Raw step output text |\n| DELETE | `/api/runs/{id}/container` | `handleAPIDeleteContainer()` | Delete retained container |\n| GET | `/api/projects/{name}/info` | `handleAPIProjectInfo()` | Docker image, version, prompt history |\n| GET | `/api/projects/{name}/info/prompt-diff` | `handleAPIPromptDiff()` | Git diff of prompt file |\n| GET | `/api/projects/{name}/workflows` | `handleAPIWorkflows()` | Workflow DAG definitions |\n| GET | `/api/projects/{name}/workflows/{workflow}/steps/{step}/content` | `handleAPIStepContent()` | Step prompt/command content |\n| GET | `/api/runs/{id}/stream` | `handleAPIStream()` | SSE log stream (live or archived) |\n| GET | `/static/*` | HTTP FileServer | Static CSS/JS assets |\n\n**Key Handler Features:**\n- **ServeHTTP()** (line 141): Delegates to internal ServeMux\n- **Template Rendering:** Uses Go's `html/template` with custom functions (stateColor, healthColor, formatTime, etc.)\n- **Static Assets:** Embedded via `//go:embed templates/*.html static/*` directive\n- **Error Handling:** JSON errors for API routes, HTML errors for page routes\n\n### Additional Context\n\n**Key Files Summary:**\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/` - 5 HTML templates (layout, projects, runs, run_detail, project_detail)\n- `/workspace/internal/domain/run.go` - Run model with state machine\n- `/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto` - gRPC service definition\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` - Daemon gRPC service implementation\n- `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go` - CLI client entrypoint\n- `/workspace/cmd/cloched/main.go` - Daemon entrypoint\n\n**Deployment:**\n- gRPC Server (port from `CLOCHE_LISTEN`, defaults to `unix:///tmp/cloche.sock`)\n- HTTP Server (port from `CLOCHE_HTTP`, optional - no default)\n- Database (SQLite at path from `CLOCHE_DB`, defaults to `cloche.db`)"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a1cb6389b0da2bc78 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 74598\ntool_uses: 26\nduration_ms: 53586</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"508569cd-e03d-4249-9b5e-689a8c858cef","uuid":"39a9ac4c-3638-4084-84ae-7d018193312a","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the codebase to understand:\n1. How the web UI is structured - find the Run Details page template/handler\n2. How 'cloche stop' works - find the stop command, gRPC service, and daemon handler\n3. What states a run can be in (running/pending vs terminal states)\n4. How the web server routes are set up\n\nSearch for:\n- Web UI templates (HTML files)\n- Web handler files\n- Stop/cancel related code\n- Run state/status types\n- HTTP route definitions\n\nBe very thorough - check all relevant files.","agentId":"a1cb6389b0da2bc78","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now let me create a comprehensive summary document of my findings.\n\n## Summary of Cloche Codebase Exploration\n\nI've completed a thorough exploration of the Cloche codebase. Here are my findings for the four key areas you requested:\n\n### 1. **Web UI Structure - Run Details Page**\n\n**Template Location:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/run_detail.html`\n\nThe Run Details page is structured as follows:\n- **Main Template Block:** `{{define \"content\"}}` (lines 1-72)\n- **Layout:** Inherits from `layout.html` which provides HTML structure with navbar and main container\n- **Dynamic Elements:**\n  - Run metadata section (title, workflow, state badge, container status, error message)\n  - Steps table with accordion-s