{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01CsfjVBYVCzaizwdszvvCzQ","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→{{define \"content\"}}\n     2→<h1>\n     3→    <a href=\"/runs\">Runs</a> / {{.Run.ID}}\n     4→    <span class=\"badge badge-{{stateColor .Run.State}}\">{{.Run.State}}</span>\n     5→</h1>\n     6→\n     7→<div class=\"run-meta\">\n     8→    <dl>\n     9→        {{if .Run.Title}}<dt>Title</dt><dd>{{.Run.Title}}</dd>{{end}}\n    10→        <dt>Workflow</dt><dd>{{.Run.WorkflowName}}</dd>\n    11→        <dt>Type</dt><dd>{{if .Run.IsHost}}host{{else}}container{{end}}</dd>\n    12→        <dt>Started</dt><dd>{{formatTime .Run.StartedAt}}</dd>\n    13→        <dt>Completed</dt><dd>{{formatTime .Run.CompletedAt}}</dd>\n    14→        <dt>Container</dt><dd class=\"mono\">{{.Run.ContainerID}}</dd>\n    15→        <dt>Container Status</dt>\n    16→        <dd id=\"container-status\">\n    17→            {{if eq .ContainerState \"running\"}}\n    18→                <span class=\"badge badge-running\">Container running</span>\n    19→            {{else if eq .ContainerState \"stopped\"}}\n    20→                <span class=\"badge badge-stopped\">Container stopped</span>\n    21→                {{if or (eq .Run.State \"succeeded\") (eq .Run.State \"failed\") (eq .Run.State \"cancelled\")}}\n    22→                <button class=\"btn btn-danger btn-sm\" id=\"delete-container-btn\" onclick=\"deleteContainer('{{.Run.ID}}')\">Delete Container</button>\n    23→                {{end}}\n    24→            {{else if eq .ContainerState \"available\"}}\n    25→                <span class=\"badge badge-succeeded\">Container available</span>\n    26→                <button class=\"btn btn-danger btn-sm\" id=\"delete-container-btn\" onclick=\"deleteContainer('{{.Run.ID}}')\">Delete Container</button>\n    27→            {{else}}\n    28→                <span class=\"badge badge-pending\">Container removed</span>\n    29→            {{end}}\n    30→        </dd>\n    31→    </dl>\n    32→</div>\n    33→\n    34→{{if .Run.ErrorMessage}}\n    35→<div class=\"error-box\">{{.Run.ErrorMessage}}</div>\n    36→{{end}}\n    37→\n    38→<h2>Steps</h2>\n    39→<table class=\"runs-table\">\n    40→    <thead>\n    41→        <tr>\n    42→            <th>Step</th>\n    43→            <th>Result</th>\n    44→            <th>Started</th>\n    45→            <th>Duration</th>\n    46→        </tr>\n    47→    </thead>\n    48→    <tbody id=\"steps-body\">\n    49→    {{if .Steps}}\n    50→        {{range .Steps}}\n    51→        <tr class=\"step-row\" data-run-id=\"{{$.Run.ID}}\" data-step=\"{{.StepName}}\" data-index=\"{{.Index}}\">\n    52→            <td>{{.StepName}}</td>\n    53→            <td>{{if .Result}}<span class=\"badge badge-{{if eq .Result \"success\"}}succeeded{{else if eq .Result \"fail\"}}failed{{else}}pending{{end}}\">{{.Result}}</span>{{else}}<span class=\"badge badge-running\">running</span>{{end}}</td>\n    54→            <td>{{formatTime .StartedAt}}</td>\n    55→            <td>{{.Duration}}</td>\n    56→        </tr>\n    57→        <tr class=\"output-row\" id=\"output-{{.Index}}\" style=\"display:none\">\n    58→            <td colspan=\"4\"><pre class=\"step-output\">Loading...</pre></td>\n    59→        </tr>\n    60→        {{end}}\n    61→    {{else}}\n    62→        <tr><td colspan=\"4\" class=\"empty\">No step executions recorded.</td></tr>\n    63→    {{end}}\n    64→    </tbody>\n    65→</table>\n    66→\n    67→<h2>\n    68→    Log\n    69→    <span id=\"log-status\" class=\"badge badge-running\" style=\"font-size:0.7rem; margin-left:0.5rem;\">Live</span>\n    70→</h2>\n    71→<div id=\"log-viewer\" class=\"log-viewer\"><pre id=\"log-content\"></pre></div>\n    72→{{end}}\n    73→\n    74→{{define \"scripts\"}}\n    75→<script>\n    76→(function() {\n    77→    var runState = '{{.Run.State}}';\n    78→    var runID = '{{.Run.ID}}';\n    79→\n    80→    // --- Log Viewer ---\n    81→    var logContent = document.getElementById('log-content');\n    82→    var logViewer = document.getElementById('log-viewer');\n    83→    var logStatus = document.getElementById('log-status');\n    84→    var autoScroll = true;\n    85→\n    86→    // Track scroll position to enable/disable auto-scroll\n    87→    logViewer.addEventListener('scroll', function() {\n    88→        var atBottom = logViewer.scrollHeight - logViewer.scrollTop - logViewer.clientHeight < 40;\n    89→        autoScroll = atBottom;\n    90→    });\n    91→\n    92→    function appendLogLine(line) {\n    93→        var span = document.createElement('span');\n    94→        span.className = 'log-line log-type-' + (line.type || 'script');\n    95→        span.textContent = '[' + line.timestamp + '] [' + line.type + '] ' + line.content + '\\n';\n    96→        logContent.appendChild(span);\n    97→        if (autoScroll) {\n    98→            logViewer.scrollTop = logViewer.scrollHeight;\n    99→        }\n   100→    }\n   101→\n   102→    function markComplete() {\n   103→        logStatus.textContent = 'Complete';\n   104→        logStatus.className = 'badge badge-succeeded';\n   105→    }\n   106→\n   107→    // Connect to SSE stream\n   108→    var source = new EventSource('/api/runs/' + runID + '/stream');\n   109→    source.onmessage = function(e) {\n   110→        try {\n   111→            var line = JSON.parse(e.data);\n   112→            appendLogLine(line);\n   113→        } catch(err) {}\n   114→    };\n   115→    source.addEventListener('done', function(e) {\n   116→        markComplete();\n   117→        source.close();\n   118→    });\n   119→    source.onerror = function() {\n   120→        markComplete();\n   121→        source.close();\n   122→    };\n   123→\n   124→    // If already complete, mark the badge immediately\n   125→    if (runState === 'succeeded' || runState === 'failed' || runState === 'cancelled') {\n   126→        logStatus.textContent = 'Complete';\n   127→        logStatus.className = 'badge badge-succeeded';\n   128→    }\n   129→\n   130→    // --- Steps Polling (for active runs) ---\n   131→    if (runState !== 'succeeded' && runState !== 'failed' && runState !== 'cancelled') {\n   132→        function poll() {\n   133→            fetch('/api/runs/' + runID)\n   134→                .then(function(r) { return r.json(); })\n   135→                .then(function(data) {\n   136→                    if (data.state !== runState) {\n   137→                        location.reload();\n   138→                        return;\n   139→                    }\n   140→                    // Update container status\n   141→                    var statusEl = document.getElementById('container-status');\n   142→                    if (statusEl && data.container_state) {\n   143→                        var cs = data.container_state;\n   144→                        if (cs === 'running') {\n   145→                            statusEl.innerHTML = '<span class=\"badge badge-running\">Container running</span>';\n   146→                        } else if (cs === 'stopped') {\n   147→                            var stoppedHtml = '<span class=\"badge badge-stopped\">Container stopped</span>';\n   148→                            if (data.state === 'succeeded' || data.state === 'failed' || data.state === 'cancelled') {\n   149→                                stoppedHtml += ' <button class=\"btn btn-danger btn-sm\" id=\"delete-container-btn\" onclick=\"deleteContainer(\\'' + escapeHtml(runID) + '\\')\">Delete Container</button>';\n   150→                            }\n   151→                            statusEl.innerHTML = stoppedHtml;\n   152→                        } else if (cs === 'available') {\n   153→                            statusEl.innerHTML = '<span class=\"badge badge-succeeded\">Container available</span>' +\n   154→                                ' <button class=\"btn btn-danger btn-sm\" id=\"delete-container-btn\" onclick=\"deleteContainer(\\'' + escapeHtml(runID) + '\\')\">Delete Container</button>';\n   155→                        } else {\n   156→                            statusEl.innerHTML = '<span class=\"badge badge-pending\">Container removed</span>';\n   157→                        }\n   158→                    }\n   159→                    var tbody = document.getElementById('steps-body');\n   160→                    if (!data.steps || data.steps.length === 0) {\n   161→                        tbody.innerHTML = '<tr><td colspan=\"4\" class=\"empty\">No step executions recorded.</td></tr>';\n   162→                        return;\n   163→                    }\n   164→\n   165→                    // Capture current accordion state before updating\n   166→                    var openAccordions = {};\n   167→                    var loadedOutputs = {};\n   168→                    var outputRows = tbody.querySelectorAll('.output-row');\n   169→                    for (var j = 0; j < outputRows.length; j++) {\n   170→                        var id = outputRows[j].id;\n   171→                        if (outputRows[j].style.display !== 'none') {\n   172→                            openAccordions[id] = true;\n   173→                        }\n   174→                        var pre = outputRows[j].querySelector('.step-output');\n   175→                        if (pre && pre.textContent !== 'Loading...') {\n   176→                            loadedOutputs[id] = pre.textContent;\n   177→                        }\n   178→                    }\n   179→\n   180→                    // Build updated step rows, preserving accordion state\n   181→                    var html = '';\n   182→                    for (var i = 0; i < data.steps.length; i++) {\n   183→                        var s = data.steps[i];\n   184→                        var badge = '';\n   185→                        if (s.result) {\n   186→                            var cls = s.result === 'success' ? 'succeeded' : s.result === 'fail' ? 'failed' : 'pending';\n   187→                            badge = '<span class=\"badge badge-' + cls + '\">' + escapeHtml(s.result) + '</span>';\n   188→                        } else {\n   189→                            badge = '<span class=\"badge badge-running\">running</span>';\n   190→                        }\n   191→                        var outputId = 'output-' + i;\n   192→                        var isOpen = openAccordions[outputId];\n   193→                        html += '<tr class=\"step-row\" data-run-id=\"' + escapeHtml(runID) + '\" data-step=\"' + escapeHtml(s.step_name) + '\" data-index=\"' + i + '\">' +\n   194→                            '<td>' + escapeHtml(s.step_name) + '</td>' +\n   195→                            '<td>' + badge + '</td>' +\n   196→                            '<td>' + s.started_at + '</td>' +\n   197→                            '<td>' + s.duration + '</td>' +\n   198→                            '</tr>' +\n   199→                            '<tr class=\"output-row\" id=\"' + outputId + '\"' + (isOpen ? '' : ' style=\"display:none\"') + '>' +\n   200→                            '<td colspan=\"4\"><pre class=\"step-output\">Loading...</pre></td>' +\n   201→                            '</tr>';\n   202→                    }\n   203→                    tbody.innerHTML = html;\n   204→\n   205→                    // Restore loaded output content for open accordions\n   206→                    for (var key in loadedOutputs) {\n   207→                        var row = document.getElementById(key);\n   208→                        if (row) {\n   209→                            var pre = row.querySelector('.step-output');\n   210→                            if (pre) {\n   211→                                pre.textContent = loadedOutputs[key];\n   212→                            }\n   213→                        }\n   214→                    }\n   215→\n   216→                    // Re-fetch output for accordions that were open but had no cached content\n   217→                    for (var key in openAccordions) {\n   218→                        if (!loadedOutputs[key]) {\n   219→                            var row = document.getElementById(key);\n   220→                            if (row) {\n   221→                                var stepRow = row.previousElementSibling;\n   222→                                if (stepRow && stepRow.dataset.runId && stepRow.dataset.step) {\n   223→                                    (function(r, rid, sname) {\n   224→                                        var pre = r.querySelector('.step-output');\n   225→                                        fetch('/api/runs/' + rid + '/steps/' + sname + '/output')\n   226→                                            .then(function(resp) {\n   227→                                                if (!resp.ok) return 'No output available.';\n   228→                                                return resp.text();\n   229→                                            })\n   230→                                            .then(function(text) { pre.textContent = text; })\n   231→                                            .catch(function() { pre.textContent = 'Failed to load output.'; });\n   232→                                    })(row, stepRow.dataset.runId, stepRow.dataset.step);\n   233→                                }\n   234→                            }\n   235→                        }\n   236→                    }\n   237→                })\n   238→                .catch(function() {});\n   239→        }\n   240→        setInterval(poll, 2000);\n   241→    }\n   242→\n   243→    function escapeHtml(s) {\n   244→        if (!s) return '';\n   245→        var d = document.createElement('div');\n   246→        d.appendChild(document.createTextNode(s));\n   247→        return d.innerHTML;\n   248→    }\n   249→})();\n   250→\n   251→// Delete container\n   252→    window.deleteContainer = function(runID) {\n   253→        var btn = document.getElementById('delete-container-btn');\n   254→        if (btn) btn.disabled = true;\n   255→        fetch('/api/runs/' + runID + '/container', { method: 'DELETE' })\n   256→            .then(function(r) { return r.json().then(function(d) { return {ok: r.ok, data: d}; }); })\n   257→            .then(function(res) {\n   258→                var statusEl = document.getElementById('container-status');\n   259→                if (res.ok) {\n   260→                    statusEl.innerHTML = '<span class=\"badge badge-pending\">Container removed</span>';\n   261→                } else {\n   262→                    if (btn) btn.disabled = false;\n   263→                    alert('Failed to delete container: ' + (res.data.error || 'unknown error'));\n   264→                }\n   265→            })\n   266→            .catch(function() {\n   267→                if (btn) btn.disabled = false;\n   268→                alert('Failed to delete container');\n   269→            });\n   270→    };\n   271→\n   272→    // Toggle step output rows\n   273→document.addEventListener('click', function(e) {\n   274→    var row = e.target.closest('.step-row');\n   275→    if (!row) return;\n   276→    var idx = row.dataset.index;\n   277→    var outputRow = document.getElementById('output-' + idx);\n   278→    if (!outputRow) return;\n   279→\n   280→    if (outputRow.style.display === 'none') {\n   281→        outputRow.style.display = '';\n   282→        var pre = outputRow.querySelector('.step-output');\n   283→        if (pre.textContent === 'Loading...') {\n   284→            var runId = row.dataset.runId;\n   285→            var step = row.dataset.step;\n   286→            fetch('/api/runs/' + runId + '/steps/' + step + '/output')\n   287→                .then(function(r) {\n   288→                    if (!r.ok) return 'No output available.';\n   289→                    return r.text();\n   290→                })\n   291→                .then(function(text) { pre.textContent = text; })\n   292→                .catch(function() { pre.textContent = 'Failed to load output.'; });\n   293→        }\n   294→    } else {\n   295→        outputRow.style.display = 'none';\n   296→    }\n   297→});\n   298→</script>\n   299→{{end}}\n   300→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"508569cd-e03d-4249-9b5e-689a8c858cef","uuid":"63b45b10-405a-4f1a-9fad-49b3bea30e85","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/run_detail.html","content":"{{define \"content\"}}\n<h1>\n    <a href=\"/runs\">Runs</a> / {{.Run.ID}}\n    <span class=\"badge badge-{{stateColor .Run.State}}\">{{.Run.State}}</span>\n</h1>\n\n<div class=\"run-meta\">\n    <dl>\n        {{if .Run.Title}}<dt>Title</dt><dd>{{.Run.Title}}</dd>{{end}}\n        <dt>Workflow</dt><dd>{{.Run.WorkflowName}}</dd>\n        <dt>Type</dt><dd>{{if .Run.IsHost}}host{{else}}container{{end}}</dd>\n        <dt>Started</dt><dd>{{formatTime .Run.StartedAt}}</dd>\n        <dt>Completed</dt><dd>{{formatTime .Run.CompletedAt}}</dd>\n        <dt>Container</dt><dd class=\"mono\">{{.Run.ContainerID}}</dd>\n        <dt>Container Status</dt>\n        <dd id=\"container-status\">\n            {{if eq .ContainerState \"running\"}}\n                <span class=\"badge badge-running\">Container running</span>\n            {{else if eq .ContainerState \"stopped\"}}\n                <span class=\"badge badge-stopped\">Container stopped</span>\n                {{if or (eq .Run.State \"succeeded\") (eq .Run.State \"failed\") (eq .Run.State \"cancelled\")}}\n                <button class=\"btn btn-danger btn-sm\" id=\"delete-container-btn\" onclick=\"deleteContainer('{{.Run.ID}}')\">Delete Container</button>\n                {{end}}\n            {{else if eq .ContainerState \"available\"}}\n                <span class=\"badge badge-succeeded\">Container available</span>\n                <button class=\"btn btn-danger btn-sm\" id=\"delete-container-btn\" onclick=\"deleteContainer('{{.Run.ID}}')\">Delete Container</button>\n            {{else}}\n                <span class=\"badge badge-pending\">Container removed</span>\n            {{end}}\n        </dd>\n    </dl>\n</div>\n\n{{if .Run.ErrorMessage}}\n<div class=\"error-box\">{{.Run.ErrorMessage}}</div>\n{{end}}\n\n<h2>Steps</h2>\n<table class=\"runs-table\">\n    <thead>\n        <tr>\n            <th>Step</th>\n            <th>Result</th>\n            <th>Started</th>\n            <th>Duration</th>\n        </tr>\n    </thead>\n    <tbody id=\"steps-body\">\n    {{if .Steps}}\n        {{range .Steps}}\n        <tr class=\"step-row\" data-run-id=\"{{$.Run.ID}}\" data-step=\"{{.StepName}}\" data-index=\"{{.Index}}\">\n            <td>{{.StepName}}</td>\n            <td>{{if .Result}}<span class=\"badge badge-{{if eq .Result \"success\"}}succeeded{{else if eq .Result \"fail\"}}failed{{else}}pending{{end}}\">{{.Result}}</span>{{else}}<span class=\"badge badge-running\">running</span>{{end}}</td>\n            <td>{{formatTime .StartedAt}}</td>\n            <td>{{.Duration}}</td>\n        </tr>\n        <tr class=\"output-row\" id=\"output-{{.Index}}\" style=\"display:none\">\n            <td colspan=\"4\"><pre class=\"step-output\">Loading...</pre></td>\n        </tr>\n        {{end}}\n    {{else}}\n        <tr><td colspan=\"4\" class=\"empty\">No step executions recorded.</td></tr>\n    {{end}}\n    </tbody>\n</table>\n\n<h2>\n    Log\n    <span id=\"log-status\" class=\"badge badge-running\" style=\"font-size:0.7rem; margin-left:0.5rem;\">Live</span>\n</h2>\n<div id=\"log-viewer\" class=\"log-viewer\"><pre id=\"log-content\"></pre></div>\n{{end}}\n\n{{define \"scripts\"}}\n<script>\n(function() {\n    var runState = '{{.Run.State}}';\n    var runID = '{{.Run.ID}}';\n\n    // --- Log Viewer ---\n    var logContent = document.getElementById('log-content');\n    var logViewer = document.getElementById('log-viewer');\n    var logStatus = document.getElementById('log-status');\n    var autoScroll = true;\n\n    // Track scroll position to enable/disable auto-scroll\n    logViewer.addEventListener('scroll', function() {\n        var atBottom = logViewer.scrollHeight - logViewer.scrollTop - logViewer.clientHeight < 40;\n        autoScroll = atBottom;\n    });\n\n    function appendLogLine(line) {\n        var span = document.createElement('span');\n        span.className = 'log-line log-type-' + (line.type || 'script');\n        span.textContent = '[' + line.timestamp + '] [' + line.type + '] ' + line.content + '\\n';\n        logContent.appendChild(span);\n        if (autoScroll) {\n            logViewer.scrollTop = logViewer.scrollHeight;\n        }\n    }\n\n    function markComplete() {\n        logStatus.textContent = 'Complete';\n        logStatus.className = 'badge badge-succeeded';\n    }\n\n    // Connect to SSE stream\n    var source = new EventSource('/api/runs/' + runID + '/stream');\n    source.onmessage = function(e) {\n        try {\n            var line = JSON.parse(e.data);\n            appendLogLine(line);\n        } catch(err) {}\n    };\n    source.addEventListener('done', function(e) {\n        markComplete();\n        source.close();\n    });\n    source.onerror = function() {\n        markComplete();\n        source.close();\n    };\n\n    // If already complete, mark the badge immediately\n    if (runState === 'succeeded' || runState === 'failed' || runState === 'cancelled') {\n        logStatus.textContent = 'Complete';\n        logStatus.className = 'badge badge-succeeded';\n    }\n\n    // --- Steps Polling (for active runs) ---\n    if (runState !== 'succeeded' && runState !== 'failed' && runState !== 'cancelled') {\n        function poll() {\n            fetch('/api/runs/' + runID)\n                .then(function(r) { return r.json(); })\n                .then(function(data) {\n                    if (data.state !== runState) {\n                        location.reload();\n                        return;\n                    }\n                    // Update container status\n                    var statusEl = document.getElementById('container-status');\n                    if (statusEl && data.container_state) {\n                        var cs = data.container_state;\n                        if (cs === 'running') {\n                            statusEl.innerHTML = '<span class=\"badge badge-running\">Container running</span>';\n                        } else if (cs === 'stopped') {\n                            var stoppedHtml = '<span class=\"badge badge-stopped\">Container stopped</span>';\n                            if (data.state === 'succeeded' || data.state === 'failed' || data.state === 'cancelled') {\n                                stoppedHtml += ' <button class=\"btn btn-danger btn-sm\" id=\"delete-container-btn\" onclick=\"deleteContainer(\\'' + escapeHtml(runID) + '\\')\">Delete Container</button>';\n                            }\n                            statusEl.innerHTML = stoppedHtml;\n                        } else if (cs === 'available') {\n                            statusEl.innerHTML = '<span class=\"badge badge-succeeded\">Container available</span>' +\n                                ' <button class=\"btn btn-danger btn-sm\" id=\"delete-container-btn\" onclick=\"deleteContainer(\\'' + escapeHtml(runID) + '\\')\">Delete Container</button>';\n                        } else {\n                            statusEl.innerHTML = '<span class=\"badge badge-pending\">Container removed</span>';\n                        }\n                    }\n                    var tbody = document.getElementById('steps-body');\n                    if (!data.steps || data.steps.length === 0) {\n                        tbody.innerHTML = '<tr><td colspan=\"4\" class=\"empty\">No step executions recorded.</td></tr>';\n                        return;\n                    }\n\n                    // Capture current accordion state before updating\n                    var openAccordions = {};\n                    var loadedOutputs = {};\n                    var outputRows = tbody.querySelectorAll('.output-row');\n                    for (var j = 0; j < outputRows.length; j++) {\n                        var id = outputRows[j].id;\n                        if (outputRows[j].style.display !== 'none') {\n                            openAccordions[id] = true;\n                        }\n                        var pre = outputRows[j].querySelector('.step-output');\n                        if (pre && pre.textContent !== 'Loading...') {\n                            loadedOutputs[id] = pre.textContent;\n                        }\n                    }\n\n                    // Build updated step rows, preserving accordion state\n                    var html = '';\n                    for (var i = 0; i < data.steps.length; i++) {\n                        var s = data.steps[i];\n                        var badge = '';\n                        if (s.result) {\n                            var cls = s.result === 'success' ? 'succeeded' : s.result === 'fail' ? 'failed' : 'pending';\n                            badge = '<span class=\"badge badge-' + cls + '\">' + escapeHtml(s.result) + '</span>';\n                        } else {\n                            badge = '<span class=\"badge badge-running\">running</span>';\n                        }\n                        var outputId = 'output-' + i;\n                        var isOpen = openAccordions[outputId];\n                        html += '<tr class=\"step-row\" data-run-id=\"' + escapeHtml(runID) + '\" data-step=\"' + escapeHtml(s.step_name) + '\" data-index=\"' + i + '\">' +\n                            '<td>' + escapeHtml(s.step_name) + '</td>' +\n                            '<td>' + badge + '</td>' +\n                            '<td>' + s.started_at + '</td>' +\n                            '<td>' + s.duration + '</td>' +\n                            '</tr>' +\n                            '<tr class=\"output-row\" id=\"' + outputId + '\"' + (isOpen ? '' : ' style=\"display:none\"') + '>' +\n                            '<td colspan=\"4\"><pre class=\"step-output\">Loading...</pre></td>' +\n                            '</tr>';\n                    }\n                    tbody.innerHTML = html;\n\n                    // Restore loaded output content for open accordions\n                    for (var key in loadedOutputs) {\n                        var row = document.getElementById(key);\n                        if (row) {\n                            var pre = row.querySelector('.step-output');\n                            if (pre) {\n                                pre.textContent = loadedOutputs[key];\n                            }\n                        }\n                    }\n\n                    // Re-fetch output for accordions that were open but had no cached content\n                    for (var key in openAccordions) {\n                        if (!loadedOutputs[key]) {\n                            var row = document.getElementById(key);\n                            if (row) {\n                                var stepRow = row.previousElementSibling;\n                                if (stepRow && stepRow.dataset.runId && stepRow.dataset.step) {\n                                    (function(r, rid, sname) {\n                                        var pre = r.querySelector('.step-output');\n                                        fetch('/api/runs/' + rid + '/steps/' + sname + '/output')\n                                            .then(function(resp) {\n                                                if (!resp.ok) return 'No output available.';\n                                                return resp.text();\n                                            })\n                                            .then(function(text) { pre.textContent = text; })\n                                            .catch(function() { pre.textContent = 'Failed to load output.'; });\n                                    })(row, stepRow.dataset.runId, stepRow.dataset.step);\n                                }\n                            }\n                        }\n                    }\n                })\n                .catch(function() {});\n        }\n        setInterval(poll, 2000);\n    }\n\n    function escapeHtml(s) {\n        if (!s) return '';\n        var d = document.createElement('div');\n        d.appendChild(document.createTextNode(s));\n        return d.innerHTML;\n    }\n})();\n\n// Delete container\n    window.deleteContainer = function(runID) {\n        var btn = document.getElementById('delete-container-btn');\n        if (btn) btn.disabled = true;\n        fetch('/api/runs/' + runID + '/container', { method: 'DELETE' })\n            .then(function(r) { return r.json().then(function(d) { return {ok: r.ok, data: d}; }); })\n            .then(function(res) {\n                var statusEl = document.getElementById('container-status');\n                if (res.ok) {\n                    statusEl.innerHTML = '<span class=\"badge badge-pending\">Container removed</span>';\n                } else {\n                    if (btn) btn.disabled = false;\n                    alert('Failed to delete container: ' + (res.data.error || 'unknown error'));\n                }\n            })\n            .catch(function() {\n                if (btn) btn.disabled = false;\n                alert('Failed to delete container');\n            });\n    };\n\n    // Toggle step output rows\ndocument.addEventListener('click', function(e) {\n    var row = e.target.closest('.step-row');\n    if (!row) return;\n    var idx = row.dataset.index;\n    var outputRow = document.getElementById('output-' + idx);\n    if (!outputRow) return;\n\n    if (outputRow.style.display === 'none') {\n        outputRow.style.display = '';\n        var pre = outputRow.querySelector('.step-output');\n        if (pre.textContent === 'Loading...') {\n            var runId = row.dataset.runId;\n            var step = row.dataset.step;\n            fetch('/api/runs/' + runId + '/steps/' + step + '/output')\n                .then(function(r) {\n                    if (!r.ok) return 'No output available.';\n                    return r.text();\n                })\n                .then(function(text) { pre.textContent = text; })\n                .catch(function() { pre.textContent = 'Failed to load output.'; });\n        }\n    } else {\n        outputRow.style.display = 'none';\n    }\n});\n</script>\n{{end}}\n","numLines":300,"startLine":1,"totalLines":300}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01MfRdBvYzkFDnSX7NL7dDQA","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01HndxV9HrSoLms7gfbkdjUb","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2815,"cache_read_input_tokens":14196,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2815},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"508569cd-e03d-4249-9b5e-689a8c858cef","uuid":"6a038a24-fcd7-4fc4-b175-36fb49185de4"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01HndxV9HrSoLms7gfbkdjUb","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package web\n     2→\n     3→import (\n     4→\t\"bufio\"\n     5→\t\"context\"\n     6→\t\"embed\"\n     7→\t\"encoding/json\"\n     8→\t\"fmt\"\n     9→\t\"html/template\"\n    10→\t\"io/fs\"\n    11→\t\"net/http\"\n    12→\t\"net/url\"\n    13→\t\"os\"\n    14→\t\"os/exec\"\n    15→\t\"path/filepath\"\n    16→\t\"regexp\"\n    17→\t\"sort\"\n    18→\t\"strconv\"\n    19→\t\"strings\"\n    20→\t\"time\"\n    21→\n    22→\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/domain\"\n    23→\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/dsl\"\n    24→\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/logstream\"\n    25→\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/ports\"\n    26→)\n    27→\n    28→// HandlerOption configures optional Handler dependencies.\n    29→type HandlerOption func(*Handler)\n    30→\n    31→// WithContainerLogger sets the container runtime for fetching live logs.\n    32→func WithContainerLogger(c ContainerLogger) HandlerOption {\n    33→\treturn func(h *Handler) { h.container = c }\n    34→}\n    35→\n    36→// WithContainerManager sets a full container manager (logs, inspect, remove).\n    37→func WithContainerManager(c ContainerManager) HandlerOption {\n    38→\treturn func(h *Handler) { h.container = c }\n    39→}\n    40→\n    41→// WithLogBroadcaster sets the log broadcaster for SSE streaming.\n    42→func WithLogBroadcaster(b *logstream.Broadcaster) HandlerOption {\n    43→\treturn func(h *Handler) { h.logBroadcast = b }\n    44→}\n    45→\n    46→// WithLogStore sets the log store for indexed log file lookups.\n    47→func WithLogStore(ls ports.LogStore) HandlerOption {\n    48→\treturn func(h *Handler) { h.logStore = ls }\n    49→}\n    50→\n    51→//go:embed templates/*.html static/*\n    52→var content embed.FS\n    53→\n    54→// Handler serves the web dashboard.\n    55→// ContainerLogger can retrieve logs from a container by ID.\n    56→type ContainerLogger interface {\n    57→\tLogs(ctx context.Context, containerID string) (string, error)\n    58→}\n    59→\n    60→// ContainerManager extends ContainerLogger with container lifecycle operations.\n    61→type ContainerManager interface {\n    62→\tContainerLogger\n    63→\tRemove(ctx context.Context, containerID string) error\n    64→\tInspect(ctx context.Context, containerID string) (*ports.ContainerStatus, error)\n    65→}\n    66→\n    67→type Handler struct {\n    68→\tstore        ports.RunStore\n    69→\tcaptures     ports.CaptureStore\n    70→\tlogStore     ports.LogStore\n    71→\tcontainer    ContainerLogger\n    72→\tlogBroadcast *logstream.Broadcaster\n    73→\tpages        map[string]*template.Template\n    74→\tmux          *http.ServeMux\n    75→}\n    76→\n    77→// NewHandler creates a web dashboard handler.\n    78→func NewHandler(store ports.RunStore, captures ports.CaptureStore, opts ...HandlerOption) (*Handler, error) {\n    79→\tfuncMap := template.FuncMap{\n    80→\t\t\"stateColor\":       stateColor,\n    81→\t\t\"healthColor\":      healthColor,\n    82→\t\t\"formatTime\":       formatTime,\n    83→\t\t\"formatDuration\":   formatDuration,\n    84→\t\t\"truncate\":         truncate,\n    85→\t\t\"shortContainerID\": shortContainerID,\n    86→\t}\n    87→\n    88→\tbase, err := template.New(\"\").Funcs(funcMap).ParseFS(content, \"templates/layout.html\")\n    89→\tif err != nil {\n    90→\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"parse layout: %w\", err)\n    91→\t}\n    92→\n    93→\tpages := map[string]*template.Template{}\n    94→\tfor _, page := range []string{\"projects\", \"runs\", \"run_detail\", \"project_detail\"} {\n    95→\t\tclone, err := base.Clone()\n    96→\t\tif err != nil {\n    97→\t\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"clone layout for %s: %w\", page, err)\n    98→\t\t}\n    99→\t\t_, err = clone.ParseFS(content, \"templates/\"+page+\".html\")\n   100→\t\tif err != nil {\n   101→\t\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"parse %s: %w\", page, err)\n   102→\t\t}\n   103→\t\tpages[page] = clone\n   104→\t}\n   105→\n   106→\th := &Handler{\n   107→\t\tstore:    store,\n   108→\t\tcaptures: captures,\n   109→\t\tpages:    pages,\n   110→\t\tmux:      http.NewServeMux(),\n   111→\t}\n   112→\tfor _, opt := range opts {\n   113→\t\topt(h)\n   114→\t}\n   115→\n   116→\tstaticFS, err := fs.Sub(content, \"static\")\n   117→\tif err != nil {\n   118→\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"static sub-fs: %w\", err)\n   119→\t}\n   120→\n   121→\th.mux.HandleFunc(\"GET /{$}\", h.handleProjectOverview)\n   122→\th.mux.HandleFunc(\"GET /projects/{name}/runs\", h.handleProjectRuns)\n   123→\th.mux.HandleFunc(\"GET /runs\", h.handleRunsList)\n   124→\th.mux.HandleFunc(\"GET /runs/{id}\", h.handleRunDetail)\n   125→\th.mux.HandleFunc(\"GET /projects/{name}\", h.handleProjectDetail)\n   126→\th.mux.HandleFunc(\"GET /api/projects\", h.handleAPIProjects)\n   127→\th.mux.HandleFunc(\"GET /api/runs\", h.handleAPIRuns)\n   128→\th.mux.HandleFunc(\"GET /api/runs/{id}\", h.handleAPIRunDetail)\n   129→\th.mux.HandleFunc(\"GET /api/runs/{id}/steps/{step}/output\", h.handleAPIStepOutput)\n   130→\th.mux.HandleFunc(\"DELETE /api/runs/{id}/container\", h.handleAPIDeleteContainer)\n   131→\th.mux.HandleFunc(\"GET /api/projects/{name}/info\", h.handleAPIProjectInfo)\n   132→\th.mux.HandleFunc(\"GET /api/projects/{name}/info/prompt-diff\", h.handleAPIPromptDiff)\n   133→\th.mux.HandleFunc(\"GET /api/projects/{name}/workflows\", h.handleAPIWorkflows)\n   134→\th.mux.HandleFunc(\"GET /api/projects/{name}/workflows/{workflow}/steps/{step}/content\", h.handleAPIStepContent)\n   135→\th.mux.HandleFunc(\"GET /api/runs/{id}/stream\", h.handleAPIStream)\n   136→\th.mux.Handle(\"GET /static/\", http.StripPrefix(\"/static/\", http.FileServerFS(staticFS)))\n   137→\n   138→\treturn h, nil\n   139→}\n   140→\n   141→func (h *Handler) ServeHTTP(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n   142→\th.mux.ServeHTTP(w, r)\n   143→}\n   144→\n   145→// --- HTML handlers ---\n   146→\n   147→// projectOverviewEntry holds data for a single project card on the landing page.\n   148→type projectOverviewEntry struct {\n   149→\tDir         string\n   150→\tLabel       string\n   151→\tHealth      domain.HealthResult\n   152→\tRecentRuns  []recentRunDot\n   153→\tActiveCount int\n   154→}\n   155→\n   156→// recentRunDot is a minimal representation of a run for the mini history display.\n   157→type recentRunDot struct {\n   158→\tID    string\n   159→\tState string\n   160→}\n   161→\n   162→const healthWindowSize = 10\n   163→\n   164→func (h *Handler) handleProjectOverview(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n   165→\tprojects, _ := h.store.ListProjects(r.Context())\n   166→\tlabels := projectLabels(projects)\n   167→\n   168→\tvar entries []projectOverviewEntry\n   169→\tfor _, dir := range projects {\n   170→\t\truns, err := h.store.ListRunsByProject(r.Context(), dir, time.Time{})\n   171→\t\tif err != nil {\n   172→\t\t\tcontinue\n   173→\t\t}\n   174→\n   175→\t\t// Convert []*domain.Run to []domain.Run for CalculateHealth.\n   176→\t\trunValues := make([]domain.Run, len(runs))\n   177→\t\tfor i, rr := range runs {\n   178→\t\t\trunValues[i] = *rr\n   179→\t\t}\n   180→\n   181→\t\thealth := domain.CalculateHealth(runValues, healthWindowSize)\n   182→\n   183→\t\t// Take the last N runs for the mini history (most recent first).\n   184→\t\tn := healthWindowSize\n   185→\t\tif n > len(runs) {\n   186→\t\t\tn = len(runs)\n   187→\t\t}\n   188→\t\tdots := make([]recentRunDot, n)\n   189→\t\tfor i := 0; i < n; i++ {\n   190→\t\t\tdots[i] = recentRunDot{\n   191→\t\t\t\tID:    runs[i].ID,\n   192→\t\t\t\tState: string(runs[i].State),\n   193→\t\t\t}\n   194→\t\t}\n   195→\n   196→\t\tvar activeCount int\n   197→\t\tfor _, rr := range runs {\n   198→\t\t\tif rr.State == domain.RunStatePending || rr.State == domain.RunStateRunning {\n   199→\t\t\t\tactiveCount++\n   200→\t\t\t}\n   201→\t\t}\n   202→\n   203→\t\tentries = append(entries, projectOverviewEntry{\n   204→\t\t\tDir:         dir,\n   205→\t\t\tLabel:       labels[dir],\n   206→\t\t\tHealth:      health,\n   207→\t\t\tRecentRuns:  dots,\n   208→\t\t\tActiveCount: activeCount,\n   209→\t\t})\n   210→\t}\n   211→\n   212→\tsort.Slice(entries, func(i, j int) bool {\n   213→\t\treturn entries[i].Label < entries[j].Label\n   214→\t})\n   215→\n   216→\tdata := map[string]any{\n   217→\t\t\"Title\":    \"Projects\",\n   218→\t\t\"Projects\": entries,\n   219→\t}\n   220→\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"text/html; charset=utf-8\")\n   221→\tif err := h.pages[\"projects\"].ExecuteTemplate(w, \"layout\", data); err != nil {\n   222→\t\thttp.Error(w, err.Error(), http.StatusInternalServerError)\n   223→\t}\n   224→}\n   225→\n   226→func (h *Handler) handleRunsList(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n   227→\tprojectFilter := r.URL.Query().Get(\"project\")\n   228→\n   229→\tvar runs []*domain.Run\n   230→\tvar err error\n   231→\tif projectFilter != \"\" {\n   232→\t\truns, err = h.store.ListRunsByProject(r.Context(), projectFilter, time.Time{})\n   233→\t} else {\n   234→\t\truns, err = h.store.ListRuns(r.Context(), time.Time{})\n   235→\t}\n   236→\tif err != nil {\n   237→\t\thttp.Error(w, \"failed to list runs\", http.StatusInternalServerError)\n   238→\t\treturn\n   239→\t}\n   240→\n   241→\tprojects, _ := h.store.ListProjects(r.Context())\n   242→\tlabels := projectLabels(projects)\n   243→\n   244→\t// Count retained containers per project\n   245→\tcontainerCounts := map[string]int{}\n   246→\tallRuns, _ := h.store.ListRuns(r.Context(), time.Time{})\n   247→\tfor _, run := range allRuns {\n   248→\t\tif run.ContainerKept {\n   249→\t\t\tcontainerCounts[run.ProjectDir]++\n   250→\t\t}\n   251→\t}\n   252→\n   253→\tvar projectList []projectEntry\n   254→\tfor _, dir := range projects {\n   255→\t\tprojectList = append(projectList, projectEntry{Dir: dir, Label: labels[dir], ContainerCount: containerCounts[dir]})\n   256→\t}\n   257→\tsort.Slice(projectList, func(i, j int) bool {\n   258→\t\treturn projectList[i].Label < projectList[j].Label\n   259→\t})\n   260→\n   261→\tdata := map[string]any{\n   262→\t\t\"Title\":         \"Runs\",\n   263→\t\t\"Runs\":          runs,\n   264→\t\t\"Projects\":      projectList,\n   265→\t\t\"ProjectFilter\": projectFilter,\n   266→\t\t\"ProjectLabels\": labels,\n   267→\t}\n   268→\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"text/html; charset=utf-8\")\n   269→\tif err := h.pages[\"runs\"].ExecuteTemplate(w, \"layout\", data); err != nil {\n   270→\t\thttp.Error(w, err.Error(), http.StatusInternalServerError)\n   271→\t}\n   272→}\n   273→\n   274→// handleProjectRuns redirects /projects/{name}/runs to /runs?project=<dir>.\n   275→func (h *Handler) handleProjectRuns(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n   276→\tdir, _, ok := h.resolveProjectDir(w, r)\n   277→\tif !ok {\n   278→\t\treturn\n   279→\t}\n   280→\thttp.Redirect(w, r, \"/runs?project=\"+url.QueryEscape(dir), http.StatusFound)\n   281→}\n   282→\n   283→// stepEntry is a merged view of a step execution for the template.\n   284→type stepEntry struct {\n   285→\tIndex     int\n   286→\tStepName  string\n   287→\tResult    string\n   288→\tStartedAt time.Time\n   289→\tDuration  string\n   290→}\n   291→\n   292→// mergeCaptures collapses started/completed capture pairs into single entries.\n   293→func mergeCaptures(caps []*domain.StepExecution) []stepEntry {\n   294→\tvar entries []stepEntry\n   295→\t// Track pending started rows by step name (LIFO for retries)\n   296→\tpending := map[string]*domain.StepExecution{}\n   297→\n   298→\tfor _, c := range caps {\n   299→\t\tif c.Result == \"\" {\n   300→\t\t\t// step_started row\n   301→\t\t\tpending[c.StepName] = c\n   302→\t\t\tcontinue\n   303→\t\t}\n   304→\t\t// step_completed row — merge with pending started if available\n   305→\t\tstartedAt := c.StartedAt\n   306→\t\tif started := pending[c.StepName]; started != nil {\n   307→\t\t\tstartedAt = started.StartedAt\n   308→\t\t\tdelete(pending, c.StepName)\n   309→\t\t}\n   310→\t\tentries = append(entries, stepEntry{\n   311→\t\t\tIndex:     len(entries),\n   312→\t\t\tStepName:  c.StepName,\n   313→\t\t\tResult:    c.Result,\n   314→\t\t\tStartedAt: startedAt,\n   315→\t\t\tDuration:  formatDuration(startedAt, c.CompletedAt),\n   316→\t\t})\n   317→\t}\n   318→\n   319→\t// Append any started-but-not-completed steps (still running)\n   320→\tfor _, c := range caps {\n   321→\t\tif c.Result == \"\" {\n   322→\t\t\tif _, used := pending[c.StepName]; !used {\n   323→\t\t\t\tcontinue\n   324→\t\t\t}\n   325→\t\t\tentries = append(entries, stepEntry{\n   326→\t\t\t\tIndex:     len(entries),\n   327→\t\t\t\tStepName:  c.StepName,\n   328→\t\t\t\tStartedAt: c.StartedAt,\n   329→\t\t\t})\n   330→\t\t\tdelete(pending, c.StepName)\n   331→\t\t}\n   332→\t}\n   333→\n   334→\treturn entries\n   335→}\n   336→\n   337→// containerState inspects the container for a run and returns one of:\n   338→//   - \"running\"   – container exists and is running\n   339→//   - \"stopped\"   – container exists, not running, not kept\n   340→//   - \"available\" – container exists, not running, kept (can be deleted)\n   341→//   - \"removed\"   – no container ID, no manager, or inspect failed\n   342→func (h *Handler) containerState(ctx context.Context, run *domain.Run) string {\n   343→\tif run.ContainerID == \"\" {\n   344→\t\treturn \"removed\"\n   345→\t}\n   346→\tmgr, ok := h.container.(ContainerManager)\n   347→\tif !ok {\n   348→\t\treturn \"removed\"\n   349→\t}\n   350→\tstatus, err := mgr.Inspect(ctx, run.ContainerID)\n   351→\tif err != nil {\n   352→\t\treturn \"removed\"\n   353→\t}\n   354→\tif status.Running {\n   355→\t\treturn \"running\"\n   356→\t}\n   357→\tif run.ContainerKept {\n   358→\t\treturn \"available\"\n   359→\t}\n   360→\treturn \"stopped\"\n   361→}\n   362→\n   363→func (h *Handler) handleRunDetail(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n   364→\tid := r.PathValue(\"id\")\n   365→\n   366→\trun, err := h.store.GetRun(r.Context(), id)\n   367→\tif err != nil {\n   368→\t\thttp.Error(w, \"run not found\", http.StatusNotFound)\n   369→\t\treturn\n   370→\t}\n   371→\n   372→\tcaps, err := h.captures.GetCaptures(r.Context(), id)\n   373→\tif err != nil {\n   374→\t\tcaps = nil // non-fatal\n   375→\t}\n   376→\n   377→\tsteps := mergeCaptures(caps)\n   378→\n   379→\tdata := map[string]any{\n   380→\t\t\"Title\":          \"Run \" + run.ID,\n   381→\t\t\"Run\":            run,\n   382→\t\t\"Steps\":          steps,\n   383→\t\t\"Page\":           \"detail\",\n   384→\t\t\"ContainerState\": h.containerState(r.Context(), run),\n   385→\t}\n   386→\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"text/html; charset=utf-8\")\n   387→\tif err := h.pages[\"run_detail\"].ExecuteTemplate(w, \"layout\", data); err != nil {\n   388→\t\thttp.Error(w, err.Error(), http.StatusInternalServerError)\n   389→\t}\n   390→}\n   391→\n   392→// --- JSON API handlers ---\n   393→\n   394→type apiRun struct {\n   395→\tID           string `json:\"id\"`\n   396→\tWorkflowName string `json:\"workflow_name\"`\n   397→\tProjectDir   string `json:\"project_dir\"`\n   398→\tProjectLabel string `json:\"project_label\"`\n   399→\tState        string `json:\"state\"`\n   400→\tStartedAt    string `json:\"started_at\"`\n   401→\tCompletedAt  string `json:\"completed_at\"`\n   402→\tContainerID  string `json:\"container_id\"`\n   403→\tErrorMessage string `json:\"error_message\"`\n   404→\tTitle        string `json:\"title\"`\n   405→\tIsHost       bool   `json:\"is_host\"`\n   406→}\n   407→\n   408→type apiStep struct {\n   409→\tStepName    string `json:\"step_name\"`\n   410→\tResult      string `json:\"result\"`\n   411→\tStartedAt   string `json:\"started_at\"`\n   412→\tCompletedAt string `json:\"completed_at\"`\n   413→\tDuration    string `json:\"duration\"`\n   414→}\n   415→\n   416→type apiRunDetail struct {\n   417→\tapiRun\n   418→\tContainerState string    `json:\"container_state\"`\n   419→\tSteps          []apiStep `json:\"steps\"`\n   420→}\n   421→\n   422→func toAPIRun(r *domain.Run, labels map[string]string) apiRun {\n   423→\treturn apiRun{\n   424→\t\tID:           r.ID,\n   425→\t\tWorkflowName: r.WorkflowName,\n   426→\t\tProjectDir:   r.ProjectDir,\n   427→\t\tProjectLabel: labels[r.ProjectDir],\n   428→\t\tState:        string(r.State),\n   429→\t\tStartedAt:    formatTime(r.StartedAt),\n   430→\t\tCompletedAt:  formatTime(r.CompletedAt),\n   431→\t\tContainerID:  r.ContainerID,\n   432→\t\tErrorMessage: r.ErrorMessage,\n   433→\t\tTitle:        r.Title,\n   434→\t\tIsHost:       r.IsHost,\n   435→\t}\n   436→}\n   437→\n   438→func (h *Handler) handleAPIRuns(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n   439→\tprojectFilter := r.URL.Query().Get(\"project\")\n   440→\n   441→\tvar runs []*domain.Run\n   442→\tvar err error\n   443→\tif projectFilter != \"\" {\n   444→\t\truns, err = h.store.ListRunsByProject(r.Context(), projectFilter, time.Time{})\n   445→\t} else {\n   446→\t\truns, err = h.store.ListRuns(r.Context(), time.Time{})\n   447→\t}\n   448→\tif err != nil {\n   449→\t\thttp.Error(w, \"failed to list runs\", http.StatusInternalServerError)\n   450→\t\treturn\n   451→\t}\n   452→\n   453→\tprojects, _ := h.store.ListProjects(r.Context())\n   454→\tlabels := projectLabels(projects)\n   455→\n   456→\tresult := make([]apiRun, len(runs))\n   457→\tfor i, run := range runs {\n   458→\t\tresult[i] = toAPIRun(run, labels)\n   459→\t}\n   460→\n   461→\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n   462→\tjson.NewEncoder(w).Encode(result)\n   463→}\n   464→\n   465→func (h *Handler) handleAPIProjects(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n   466→\tprojects, err := h.store.ListProjects(r.Context())\n   467→\tif err != nil {\n   468→\t\thttp.Error(w, \"failed to list projects\", http.StatusInternalServerError)\n   469→\t\treturn\n   470→\t}\n   471→\tlabels := projectLabels(projects)\n   472→\n   473→\ttype apiHealth struct {\n   474→\t\tStatus string `json:\"status\"`\n   475→\t\tPassed int    `json:\"passed\"`\n   476→\t\tFailed int    `json:\"failed\"`\n   477→\t\tTotal  int    `json:\"total\"`\n   478→\t}\n   479→\ttype apiProject struct {\n   480→\t\tDir         string    `json:\"dir\"`\n   481→\t\tLabel       string    `json:\"label\"`\n   482→\t\tHealth      apiHealth `json:\"health\"`\n   483→\t\tActiveCount int       `json:\"active_count\"`\n   484→\t}\n   485→\tresult := make([]apiProject, len(projects))\n   486→\tfor i, dir := range projects {\n   487→\t\truns, _ := h.store.ListRunsByProject(r.Context(), dir, time.Time{})\n   488→\t\trunValues := make([]domain.Run, len(runs))\n   489→\t\tfor j, rr := range runs {\n   490→\t\t\trunValues[j] = *rr\n   491→\t\t}\n   492→\t\thealth := domain.CalculateHealth(runValues, healthWindowSize)\n   493→\t\tvar activeCount int\n   494→\t\tfor _, rr := range runs {\n   495→\t\t\tif rr.State == domain.RunStatePending || rr.State == domain.RunStateRunning {\n   496→\t\t\t\tactiveCount++\n   497→\t\t\t}\n   498→\t\t}\n   499→\t\tresult[i] = apiProject{\n   500→\t\t\tDir:   dir,\n   501→\t\t\tLabel: labels[dir],\n   502→\t\t\tHealth: apiHealth{\n   503→\t\t\t\tStatus: string(health.Status),\n   504→\t\t\t\tPassed: health.Passed,\n   505→\t\t\t\tFailed: health.Failed,\n   506→\t\t\t\tTotal:  health.Total,\n   507→\t\t\t},\n   508→\t\t\tActiveCount: activeCount,\n   509→\t\t}\n   510→\t}\n   511→\n   512→\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n   513→\tjson.NewEncoder(w).Encode(result)\n   514→}\n   515→\n   516→func (h *Handler) handleAPIRunDetail(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n   517→\tid := r.PathValue(\"id\")\n   518→\n   519→\trun, err := h.store.GetRun(r.Context(), id)\n   520→\tif err != nil {\n   521→\t\thttp.Error(w, \"run not found\", http.StatusNotFound)\n   522→\t\treturn\n   523→\t}\n   524→\n   525→\tcaps, err := h.captures.GetCaptures(r.Context(), id)\n   526→\tif err != nil {\n   527→\t\tcaps = nil\n   528→\t}\n   529→\n   530→\tprojects, _ := h.store.ListProjects(r.Context())\n   531→\tlabels := projectLabels(projects)\n   532→\n   533→\tmerged := mergeCaptures(caps)\n   534→\tsteps := make([]apiStep, len(merged))\n   535→\tfor i, e := range merged {\n   536→\t\tsteps[i] = apiStep{\n   537→\t\t\tStepName:  e.StepName,\n   538→\t\t\tResult:    e.Result,\n   539→\t\t\tStartedAt: formatTime(e.StartedAt),\n   540→\t\t\tDuration:  e.Duration,\n   541→\t\t}\n   542→\t}\n   543→\n   544→\tdetail := apiRunDetail{\n   545→\t\tapiRun:         toAPIRun(run, labels),\n   546→\t\tContainerState: h.containerState(r.Context(), run),\n   547→\t\tSteps:          steps,\n   548→\t}\n   549→\n   550→\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n   551→\tjson.NewEncoder(w).Encode(detail)\n   552→}\n   553→\n   554→func (h *Handler) handleAPIStepOutput(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n   555→\tid := r.PathValue(\"id\")\n   556→\tstep := r.PathValue(\"step\")\n   557→\tlogType := r.URL.Query().Get(\"type\")   // optional: \"script\", \"llm\"\n   558→\tformat := r.URL.Query().Get(\"format\")  // optional: \"raw\" to skip parsing\n   559→\n   560→\trun, err := h.store.GetRun(r.Context(), id)\n   561→\tif err != nil {\n   562→\t\thttp.Error(w, \"run not found\", http.StatusNotFound)\n   563→\t\treturn\n   564→\t}\n   565→\n   566→\twriteOutput := func(data []byte) {\n   567→\t\tif format != \"raw\" {\n   568→\t\t\tdata = logstream.ParseClaudeStream(data)\n   569→\t\t}\n   570→\t\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"text/plain; charset=utf-8\")\n   571→\t\tw.Write(data)\n   572→\t}\n   573→\n   574→\t// Try log index first for fast lookup\n   575→\tif h.logStore != nil {\n   576→\t\tlogFiles, err := h.logStore.GetLogFilesByStep(r.Context(), id, step)\n   577→\t\tif err == nil && len(logFiles) > 0 {\n   578→\t\t\t// If type filter specified, narrow results\n   579→\t\t\tfor _, lf := range logFiles {\n   580→\t\t\t\tif logType != \"\" && lf.FileType != logType {\n   581→\t\t\t\t\tcontinue\n   582→\t\t\t\t}\n   583→\t\t\t\tdata, readErr := os.ReadFile(lf.FilePath)\n   584→\t\t\t\tif readErr == nil && len(data) > 0 {\n   585→\t\t\t\t\twriteOutput(data)\n   586→\t\t\t\t\treturn\n   587→\t\t\t\t}\n   588→\t\t\t}\n   589→\t\t}\n   590→\t}\n   591→\n   592→\toutputDir := filepath.Join(run.ProjectDir, \".cloche\", id, \"output\")\n   593→\n   594→\t// Fall back to file path conventions\n   595→\t// If type is \"llm\", try llm-<step>.log\n   596→\tif logType == \"llm\" {\n   597→\t\tllmPath := filepath.Join(outputDir, \"llm-\"+step+\".log\")\n   598→\t\tdata, err := os.ReadFile(llmPath)\n   599→\t\tif err == nil && len(data) > 0 {\n   600→\t\t\twriteOutput(data)\n   601→\t\t\treturn\n   602→\t\t}\n   603→\t}\n   604→\n   605→\t// Try per-step output first, fall back to container.log, then live docker logs\n   606→\toutputPath := filepath.Join(outputDir, step+\".log\")\n   607→\tdata, err := os.ReadFile(outputPath)\n   608→\tif err == nil && len(data) > 0 {\n   609→\t\twriteOutput(data)\n   610→\t\treturn\n   611→\t}\n   612→\n   613→\tcontainerLog := filepath.Join(outputDir, \"container.log\")\n   614→\tdata, err = os.ReadFile(containerLog)\n   615→\tif err == nil && len(data) > 0 {\n   616→\t\twriteOutput(data)\n   617→\t\treturn\n   618→\t}\n   619→\n   620→\t// Last resort: try live docker logs from still-existing container\n   621→\tif h.container != nil && run.ContainerID != \"\" {\n   622→\t\tif logs, logErr := h.container.Logs(r.Context(), run.ContainerID); logErr == nil && logs != \"\" {\n   623→\t\t\twriteOutput([]byte(logs))\n   624→\t\t\treturn\n   625→\t\t}\n   626→\t}\n   627→\n   628→\thttp.Error(w, \"step output not found\", http.StatusNotFound)\n   629→}\n   630→\n   631→func (h *Handler) handleAPIDeleteContainer(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n   632→\tid := r.PathValue(\"id\")\n   633→\n   634→\trun, err := h.store.GetRun(r.Context(), id)\n   635→\tif err != nil {\n   636→\t\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n   637→\t\tw.WriteHeader(http.StatusNotFound)\n   638→\t\tjson.NewEncoder(w).Encode(map[string]string{\"error\": \"run not found\"})\n   639→\t\treturn\n   640→\t}\n   641→\n   642→\tmgr, ok := h.container.(ContainerManager)\n   643→\tif !ok || run.ContainerID == \"\" {\n   644→\t\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n   645→\t\tw.WriteHeader(http.StatusBadRequest)\n   646→\t\tjson.NewEncoder(w).Encode(map[string]string{\"error\": \"container management not available\"})\n   647→\t\treturn\n   648→\t}\n   649→\n   650→\tif err := mgr.Remove(r.Context(), run.ContainerID); err != nil {\n   651→\t\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n   652→\t\tw.WriteHeader(http.StatusInternalServerError)\n   653→\t\tjson.NewEncoder(w).Encode(map[string]string{\"error\": fmt.Sprintf(\"failed to remove container: %v\", err)})\n   654→\t\treturn\n   655→\t}\n   656→\n   657→\trun.ContainerKept = false\n   658→\tif err := h.store.UpdateRun(r.Context(), run); err != nil {\n   659→\t\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n   660→\t\tw.WriteHeader(http.StatusInternalServerError)\n   661→\t\tjson.NewEncoder(w).Encode(map[string]string{\"error\": fmt.Sprintf(\"failed to update run: %v\", err)})\n   662→\t\treturn\n   663→\t}\n   664→\n   665→\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n   666→\tjson.NewEncoder(w).Encode(map[string]string{\"status\": \"ok\"})\n   667→}\n   668→\n   669→// handleAPIStream serves an SSE stream of log lines for a run.\n   670→// For active runs, it subscribes to the live broadcaster.\n   671→// For completed runs, it serves the archived full.log then closes.\n   672→func (h *Handler) handleAPIStream(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n   673→\tid := r.PathValue(\"id\")\n   674→\n   675→\trun, err := h.store.GetRun(r.Context(), id)\n   676→\tif err != nil {\n   677→\t\thttp.Error(w, \"run not found\", http.StatusNotFound)\n   678→\t\treturn\n   679→\t}\n   680→\n   681→\tflusher, ok := w.(http.Flusher)\n   682→\tif !ok {\n   683→\t\thttp.Error(w, \"streaming not supported\", http.StatusInternalServerError)\n   684→\t\treturn\n   685→\t}\n   686→\n   687→\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"text/event-stream\")\n   688→\tw.Header().Set(\"Cache-Control\", \"no-cache\")\n   689→\tw.Header().Set(\"Connection\", \"keep-alive\")\n   690→\tw.Header().Set(\"X-Accel-Buffering\", \"no\")\n   691→\n   692→\tisComplete := run.State == domain.RunStateSucceeded ||\n   693→\t\trun.State == domain.RunStateFailed ||\n   694→\t\trun.State == domain.RunStateCancelled\n   695→\n   696→\tif isComplete {\n   697→\t\t// Serve archived full.log\n   698→\t\th.streamFullLog(w, flusher, run)\n   699→\t\t// Send done event\n   700→\t\tfmt.Fprintf(w, \"event: done\\ndata: %s\\n\\n\", string(run.State))\n   701→\t\tflusher.Flush()\n   702→\t\treturn\n   703→\t}\n   704→\n   705→\t// Active run: subscribe to live broadcaster\n   706→\tif h.logBroadcast == nil {\n   707→\t\thttp.Error(w, \"log streaming not available\", http.StatusServiceUnavailable)\n   708→\t\treturn\n   709→\t}\n   710→\n   711→\tsub := h.logBroadcast.Subscribe(id)\n   712→\tdefer h.logBroadcast.Unsubscribe(id, sub)\n   713→\n   714→\tctx := r.Context()\n   715→\tfor {\n   716→\t\tselect {\n   717→\t\tcase <-ctx.Done():\n   718→\t\t\treturn\n   719→\t\tcase line, ok := <-sub.C:\n   720→\t\t\tif !ok {\n   721→\t\t\t\t// Stream finished (run completed)\n   722→\t\t\t\tfmt.Fprintf(w, \"event: done\\ndata: completed\\n\\n\")\n   723→\t\t\t\tflusher.Flush()\n   724→\t\t\t\treturn\n   725→\t\t\t}\n   726→\t\t\tline = parseLLMLogLine(line)\n   727→\t\t\tif line.Type == \"\" {\n   728→\t\t\t\tcontinue // skip protocol-only llm lines\n   729→\t\t\t}\n   730→\t\t\tdata, _ := json.Marshal(line)\n   731→\t\t\tfmt.Fprintf(w, \"data: %s\\n\\n\", data)\n   732→\t\t\tflusher.Flush()\n   733→\t\t}\n   734→\t}\n   735→}\n   736→\n   737→// logLineRegex parses \"[timestamp] [type] content\" format from full.log.\n   738→var logLineRegex = regexp.MustCompile(`^\\[([^\\]]+)\\] \\[([^\\]]+)\\] (.*)$`)\n   739→\n   740→// streamFullLog reads the archived full.log file and sends its entries as SSE events.\n   741→// LLM-type lines are parsed from raw Claude JSON into human-readable text.\n   742→func (h *Handler) streamFullLog(w http.ResponseWriter, flusher http.Flusher, run *domain.Run) {\n   743→\tlogPath := filepath.Join(run.ProjectDir, \".cloche\", run.ID, \"output\", \"full.log\")\n   744→\tf, err := os.Open(logPath)\n   745→\tif err != nil {\n   746→\t\treturn\n   747→\t}\n   748→\tdefer f.Close()\n   749→\n   750→\tscanner := bufio.NewScanner(f)\n   751→\tfor scanner.Scan() {\n   752→\t\ttext := scanner.Text()\n   753→\t\tline := parseFullLogLine(text)\n   754→\t\tline = parseLLMLogLine(line)\n   755→\t\tif line.Type == \"\" {\n   756→\t\t\tcontinue // skip protocol-only llm lines\n   757→\t\t}\n   758→\t\tdata, _ := json.Marshal(line)\n   759→\t\tfmt.Fprintf(w, \"data: %s\\n\\n\", data)\n   760→\t\tflusher.Flush()\n   761→\t}\n   762→}\n   763→\n   764→// parseLLMLogLine parses a LogLine whose type is \"llm\". If the content is\n   765→// Claude stream JSON, it extracts the human-readable text. Protocol-only\n   766→// events return a LogLine with an empty Type (caller should skip it).\n   767→// Non-llm lines are returned unchanged.\n   768→func parseLLMLogLine(line logstream.LogLine) logstream.LogLine {\n   769→\tif line.Type != \"llm\" {\n   770→\t\treturn line\n   771→\t}\n   772→\ttext, ok := logstream.ParseClaudeLine([]byte(line.Content))\n   773→\tif !ok {\n   774→\t\treturn logstream.LogLine{} // signal to skip\n   775→\t}\n   776→\tline.Content = text\n   777→\treturn line\n   778→}\n   779→\n   780→// parseFullLogLine parses a \"[timestamp] [type] content\" line into a LogLine.\n   781→func parseFullLogLine(text string) logstream.LogLine {\n   782→\tm := logLineRegex.FindStringSubmatch(text)\n   783→\tif m == nil {\n   784→\t\treturn logstream.LogLine{\n   785→\t\t\tTimestamp: time.Now().UTC().Format(time.RFC3339),\n   786→\t\t\tType:      \"script\",\n   787→\t\t\tContent:   text,\n   788→\t\t}\n   789→\t}\n   790→\treturn logstream.LogLine{\n   791→\t\tTimestamp: m[1],\n   792→\t\tType:      m[2],\n   793→\t\tContent:   m[3],\n   794→\t}\n   795→}\n   796→\n   797→// --- Project detail handlers ---\n   798→\n   799→// resolveProjectDir resolves a project label from the URL to its directory path.\n   800→// Returns (dir, label, ok). Writes a JSON error response if not found.\n   801→func (h *Handler) resolveProjectDir(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) (string, string, bool) {\n   802→\tlabel := r.PathValue(\"name\")\n   803→\tprojects, _ := h.store.ListProjects(r.Context())\n   804→\tlabels := projectLabels(projects)\n   805→\tfor dir, l := range labels {\n   806→\t\tif l == label {\n   807→\t\t\treturn dir, label, true\n   808→\t\t}\n   809→\t}\n   810→\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n   811→\tw.WriteHeader(http.StatusNotFound)\n   812→\tjson.NewEncoder(w).Encode(map[string]string{\"error\": \"project not found\"})\n   813→\treturn \"\", \"\", false\n   814→}\n   815→\n   816→func (h *Handler) handleProjectDetail(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n   817→\tdir, label, ok := h.resolveProjectDir(w, r)\n   818→\tif !ok {\n   819→\t\treturn\n   820→\t}\n   821→\n   822→\truns, _ := h.store.ListRunsByProject(r.Context(), dir, time.Time{})\n   823→\tn := 10\n   824→\tif n > len(runs) {\n   825→\t\tn = len(runs)\n   826→\t}\n   827→\tdots := make([]recentRunDot, n)\n   828→\tfor i := 0; i < n; i++ {\n   829→\t\tdots[i] = recentRunDot{ID: runs[i].ID, State: string(runs[i].State)}\n   830→\t}\n   831→\n   832→\tdata := map[string]any{\n   833→\t\t\"Title\":      label,\n   834→\t\t\"Label\":      label,\n   835→\t\t\"Dir\":        dir,\n   836→\t\t\"RecentRuns\": dots,\n   837→\t}\n   838→\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"text/html; charset=utf-8\")\n   839→\tif err := h.pages[\"project_detail\"].ExecuteTemplate(w, \"layout\", data); err != nil {\n   840→\t\thttp.Error(w, err.Error(), http.StatusInternalServerError)\n   841→\t}\n   842→}\n   843→\n   844→func (h *Handler) handleAPIProjectInfo(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n   845→\tdir, _, ok := h.resolveProjectDir(w, r)\n   846→\tif !ok {\n   847→\t\treturn\n   848→\t}\n   849→\n   850→\t// Docker image: read FROM line from Dockerfile\n   851→\tdockerImage := \"\"\n   852→\tdockerfilePath := filepath.Join(dir, \".cloche\", \"Dockerfile\")\n   853→\tif data, err := os.ReadFile(dockerfilePath); err == nil {\n   854→\t\t// Find the last FROM line (final stage)\n   855→\t\tfor _, line := range strings.Split(string(data), \"\\n\") {\n   856→\t\t\ttrimmed := strings.TrimSpace(line)\n   857→\t\t\tif strings.HasPrefix(strings.ToUpper(trimmed), \"FROM \") {\n   858→\t\t\t\tparts := strings.Fields(trimmed)\n   859→\t\t\t\tif len(parts) >= 2 {\n   860→\t\t\t\t\tdockerImage = parts[1]\n   861→\t\t\t\t}\n   862→\t\t\t}\n   863→\t\t}\n   864→\t}\n   865→\n   866→\t// Version\n   867→\tversion := 0\n   868→\tversionPath := filepath.Join(dir, \".cloche\", \"version\")\n   869→\tif data, err := os.ReadFile(versionPath); err == nil {\n   870→\t\tif v, err := strconv.Atoi(strings.TrimSpace(string(data))); err == nil {\n   871→\t\t\tversion = v\n   872→\t\t}\n   873→\t}\n   874→\n   875→\t// Prompt files history\n   876→\ttype commitEntry struct {\n   877→\t\tSHA     string `json:\"sha\"`\n   878→\t\tDate    string `json:\"date\"`\n   879→\t\tMessage string `json:\"message\"`\n   880→\t}\n   881→\ttype promptFile struct {\n   882→\t\tPath    string        `json:\"path\"`\n   883→\t\tHistory []commitEntry `json:\"history\"`\n   884→\t}\n   885→\n   886→\tvar promptFiles []promptFile\n   887→\tpromptsDir := filepath.Join(dir, \".cloche\", \"prompts\")\n   888→\tif entries, err := os.ReadDir(promptsDir); err == nil {\n   889→\t\tfor _, e := range entries {\n   890→\t\t\tif e.IsDir() {\n   891→\t\t\t\tcontinue\n   892→\t\t\t}\n   893→\t\t\trelPath := filepath.Join(\".cloche\", \"prompts\", e.Name())\n   894→\t\t\tcmd := exec.Command(\"git\", \"log\", \"--follow\", \"--format=%H %aI %s\", \"--\", relPath)\n   895→\t\t\tcmd.Dir = dir\n   896→\t\t\tout, err := cmd.Output()\n   897→\t\t\tif err != nil {\n   898→\t\t\t\tcontinue\n   899→\t\t\t}\n   900→\t\t\tvar history []commitEntry\n   901→\t\t\tfor _, line := range strings.Split(strings.TrimSpace(string(out)), \"\\n\") {\n   902→\t\t\t\tif line == \"\" {\n   903→\t\t\t\t\tcontinue\n   904→\t\t\t\t}\n   905→\t\t\t\tparts := strings.SplitN(line, \" \", 3)\n   906→\t\t\t\tif len(parts) < 3 {\n   907→\t\t\t\t\tcontinue\n   908→\t\t\t\t}\n   909→\t\t\t\t// Parse date to short form\n   910→\t\t\t\tdateStr := parts[1]\n   911→\t\t\t\tif t, err := time.Parse(time.RFC3339, dateStr); err == nil {\n   912→\t\t\t\t\tdateStr = t.Format(\"2006-01-02\")\n   913→\t\t\t\t}\n   914→\t\t\t\thistory = append(history, commitEntry{\n   915→\t\t\t\t\tSHA:     parts[0][:7],\n   916→\t\t\t\t\tDate:    dateStr,\n   917→\t\t\t\t\tMessage: parts[2],\n   918→\t\t\t\t})\n   919→\t\t\t}\n   920→\t\t\tpromptFiles = append(promptFiles, promptFile{Path: relPath, History: history})\n   921→\t\t}\n   922→\t}\n   923→\n   924→\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n   925→\tjson.NewEncoder(w).Encode(map[string]any{\n   926→\t\t\"docker_image\": dockerImage,\n   927→\t\t\"version\":      version,\n   928→\t\t\"prompt_files\": promptFiles,\n   929→\t})\n   930→}\n   931→\n   932→func (h *Handler) handleAPIPromptDiff(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n   933→\tdir, _, ok := h.resolveProjectDir(w, r)\n   934→\tif !ok {\n   935→\t\treturn\n   936→\t}\n   937→\tfile := r.URL.Query().Get(\"file\")\n   938→\tsha := r.URL.Query().Get(\"sha\")\n   939→\tif file == \"\" || sha == \"\" {\n   940→\t\thttp.Error(w, \"file and sha required\", http.StatusBadRequest)\n   941→\t\treturn\n   942→\t}\n   943→\n   944→\t// Validate sha is alphanumeric to prevent injection\n   945→\tfor _, c := range sha {\n   946→\t\tif !((c >= '0' && c <= '9') || (c >= 'a' && c <= 'f') || (c >= 'A' && c <= 'F')) {\n   947→\t\t\thttp.Error(w, \"invalid sha\", http.StatusBadRequest)\n   948→\t\t\treturn\n   949→\t\t}\n   950→\t}\n   951→\n   952→\tcmd := exec.Command(\"git\", \"diff\", sha+\"^..\"+sha, \"--\", file)\n   953→\tcmd.Dir = dir\n   954→\tout, err := cmd.Output()\n   955→\tif err != nil {\n   956→\t\thttp.Error(w, \"diff not available\", http.StatusNotFound)\n   957→\t\treturn\n   958→\t}\n   959→\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"text/plain; charset=utf-8\")\n   960→\tw.Write(out)\n   961→}\n   962→\n   963→func (h *Handler) handleAPIWorkflows(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n   964→\tdir, _, ok := h.resolveProjectDir(w, r)\n   965→\tif !ok {\n   966→\t\treturn\n   967→\t}\n   968→\n   969→\tclocheDir := filepath.Join(dir, \".cloche\")\n   970→\tentries, err := os.ReadDir(clocheDir)\n   971→\tif err != nil {\n   972→\t\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n   973→\t\tjson.NewEncoder(w).Encode([]any{})\n   974→\t\treturn\n   975→\t}\n   976→\n   977→\ttype apiWire struct {\n   978→\t\tFrom   string `json:\"from\"`\n   979→\t\tResult string `json:\"result\"`\n   980→\t\tTo     string `json:\"to\"`\n   981→\t}\n   982→\ttype apiStepDef struct {\n   983→\t\tName    string            `json:\"name\"`\n   984→\t\tType    string            `json:\"type\"`\n   985→\t\tResults []string          `json:\"results\"`\n   986→\t\tConfig  map[string]string `json:\"config\"`\n   987→\t}\n   988→\ttype apiWorkflow struct {\n   989→\t\tName      string       `json:\"name\"`\n   990→\t\tFile      string       `json:\"file\"`\n   991→\t\tSteps     []apiStepDef `json:\"steps\"`\n   992→\t\tWires     []apiWire    `json:\"wires\"`\n   993→\t\tEntryStep string       `json:\"entry_step\"`\n   994→\t}\n   995→\n   996→\tvar workflows []apiWorkflow\n   997→\tfor _, e := range entries {\n   998→\t\tif e.IsDir() || !strings.HasSuffix(e.Name(), \".cloche\") || e.Name() == \"host.cloche\" {\n   999→\t\t\tcontinue\n  1000→\t\t}\n  1001→\t\tdata, err := os.ReadFile(filepath.Join(clocheDir, e.Name()))\n  1002→\t\tif err != nil {\n  1003→\t\t\tcontinue\n  1004→\t\t}\n  1005→\t\twf, err := dsl.ParseForContainer(string(data))\n  1006→\t\tif err != nil {\n  1007→\t\t\tcontinue\n  1008→\t\t}\n  1009→\t\tvar steps []apiStepDef\n  1010→\t\tfor _, s := range wf.Steps {\n  1011→\t\t\tsteps = append(steps, apiStepDef{\n  1012→\t\t\t\tName:    s.Name,\n  1013→\t\t\t\tType:    string(s.Type),\n  1014→\t\t\t\tResults: s.Results,\n  1015→\t\t\t\tConfig:  s.Config,\n  1016→\t\t\t})\n  1017→\t\t}\n  1018→\t\t// Sort steps by name for consistent ordering\n  1019→\t\tsort.Slice(steps, func(i, j int) bool { return steps[i].Name < steps[j].Name })\n  1020→\n  1021→\t\tvar wires []apiWire\n  1022→\t\tfor _, wire := range wf.Wiring {\n  1023→\t\t\twires = append(wires, apiWire{From: wire.From, Result: wire.Result, To: wire.To})\n  1024→\t\t}\n  1025→\n  1026→\t\tworkflows = append(workflows, apiWorkflow{\n  1027→\t\t\tName:      wf.Name,\n  1028→\t\t\tFile:      filepath.Join(\".cloche\", e.Name()),\n  1029→\t\t\tSteps:     steps,\n  1030→\t\t\tWires:     wires,\n  1031→\t\t\tEntryStep: wf.EntryStep,\n  1032→\t\t})\n  1033→\t}\n  1034→\n  1035→\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n  1036→\tjson.NewEncoder(w).Encode(workflows)\n  1037→}\n  1038→\n  1039→func (h *Handler) handleAPIStepContent(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n  1040→\tdir, _, ok := h.resolveProjectDir(w, r)\n  1041→\tif !ok {\n  1042→\t\treturn\n  1043→\t}\n  1044→\tworkflowName := r.PathValue(\"workflow\")\n  1045→\tstepName := r.PathValue(\"step\")\n  1046→\n  1047→\t// Find the workflow file\n  1048→\tclocheDir := filepath.Join(dir, \".cloche\")\n  1049→\tvar wf *domain.Workflow\n  1050→\tentries, _ := os.ReadDir(clocheDir)\n  1051→\tfor _, e := range entries {\n  1052→\t\tif e.IsDir() || !strings.HasSuffix(e.Name(), \".cloche\") || e.Name() == \"host.cloche\" {\n  1053→\t\t\tcontinue\n  1054→\t\t}\n  1055→\t\tdata, err := os.ReadFile(filepath.Join(clocheDir, e.Name()))\n  1056→\t\tif err != nil {\n  1057→\t\t\tcontinue\n  1058→\t\t}\n  1059→\t\tparsed, err := dsl.ParseForContainer(string(data))\n  1060→\t\tif err != nil {\n  1061→\t\t\tcontinue\n  1062→\t\t}\n  1063→\t\tif parsed.Name == workflowName {\n  1064→\t\t\twf = parsed\n  1065→\t\t\tbreak\n  1066→\t\t}\n  1067→\t}\n  1068→\tif wf == nil {\n  1069→\t\thttp.Error(w, \"workflow not found\", http.StatusNotFound)\n  1070→\t\treturn\n  1071→\t}\n  1072→\n  1073→\tstep, ok := wf.Steps[stepName]\n  1074→\tif !ok {\n  1075→\t\thttp.Error(w, \"step not found\", http.StatusNotFound)\n  1076→\t\treturn\n  1077→\t}\n  1078→\n  1079→\t// Try to read the referenced file from step config\n  1080→\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"text/plain; charset=utf-8\")\n  1081→\n  1082→\tif prompt := step.Config[\"prompt\"]; prompt != \"\" {\n  1083→\t\tcontent, err := resolveFileRef(prompt, dir)\n  1084→\t\tif err == nil {\n  1085→\t\t\tw.Write([]byte(content))\n  1086→\t\t\treturn\n  1087→\t\t}\n  1088→\t}\n  1089→\tif cmd := step.Config[\"command\"]; cmd != \"\" {\n  1090→\t\tcontent, _ := resolveFileRef(cmd, dir)\n  1091→\t\tw.Write([]byte(content))\n  1092→\t\treturn\n  1093→\t}\n  1094→\tif script := step.Config[\"script\"]; script != \"\" {\n  1095→\t\tcontent, _ := resolveFileRef(script, dir)\n  1096→\t\tw.Write([]byte(content))\n  1097→\t\treturn\n  1098→\t}\n  1099→\n  1100→\thttp.Error(w, \"no content available\", http.StatusNotFound)\n  1101→}\n  1102→\n  1103→// --- Template helpers ---\n  1104→\n  1105→// resolveFileRef resolves file(\"path\") DSL syntax to actual file contents.\n  1106→// If the value uses file() syntax, the referenced file is read from disk.\n  1107→// Otherwise the value is returned as-is.\n  1108→func resolveFileRef(value, baseDir string) (string, error) {\n  1109→\tif strings.HasPrefix(value, `file(\"`) && strings.HasSuffix(value, `\")`) {\n  1110→\t\tpath := value[6 : len(value)-2]\n  1111→\t\tdata, err := os.ReadFile(filepath.Join(baseDir, path))\n  1112→\t\tif err != nil {\n  1113→\t\t\treturn \"\", err\n  1114→\t\t}\n  1115→\t\treturn string(data), nil\n  1116→\t}\n  1117→\treturn value, nil\n  1118→}\n  1119→\n  1120→func stateColor(state domain.RunState) string {\n  1121→\tswitch state {\n  1122→\tcase domain.RunStatePending:\n  1123→\t\treturn \"pending\"\n  1124→\tcase domain.RunStateRunning:\n  1125→\t\treturn \"running\"\n  1126→\tcase domain.RunStateSucceeded:\n  1127→\t\treturn \"succeeded\"\n  1128→\tcase domain.RunStateFailed:\n  1129→\t\treturn \"failed\"\n  1130→\tcase domain.RunStateCancelled:\n  1131→\t\treturn \"cancelled\"\n  1132→\tdefault:\n  1133→\t\treturn \"pending\"\n  1134→\t}\n  1135→}\n  1136→\n  1137→func healthColor(status domain.HealthStatus) string {\n  1138→\tswitch status {\n  1139→\tcase domain.HealthGreen:\n  1140→\t\treturn \"green\"\n  1141→\tcase domain.HealthYellow:\n  1142→\t\treturn \"yellow\"\n  1143→\tcase domain.HealthRed:\n  1144→\t\treturn \"red\"\n  1145→\tcase domain.HealthBlue:\n  1146→\t\treturn \"blue\"\n  1147→\tdefault:\n  1148→\t\treturn \"grey\"\n  1149→\t}\n  1150→}\n  1151→\n  1152→func formatTime(t time.Time) string {\n  1153→\tif t.IsZero() {\n  1154→\t\treturn \"\"\n  1155→\t}\n  1156→\treturn t.Format(\"2006-01-02 15:04:05\")\n  1157→}\n  1158→\n  1159→func formatDuration(start, end time.Time) string {\n  1160→\tif start.IsZero() || end.IsZero() {\n  1161→\t\treturn \"\"\n  1162→\t}\n  1163→\td := end.Sub(start)\n  1164→\tif d < time.Second {\n  1165→\t\treturn fmt.Sprintf(\"%dms\", d.Milliseconds())\n  1166→\t}\n  1167→\tif d < time.Minute {\n  1168→\t\treturn fmt.Sprintf(\"%.1fs\", d.Seconds())\n  1169→\t}\n  1170→\treturn fmt.Sprintf(\"%dm%ds\", int(d.Minutes()), int(d.Seconds())%60)\n  1171→}\n  1172→\n  1173→func truncate(s string, n int) string {\n  1174→\tif len(s) <= n {\n  1175→\t\treturn s\n  1176→\t}\n  1177→\treturn s[:n] + \"...\"\n  1178→}\n  1179→\n  1180→func shortContainerID(id string) string {\n  1181→\tif len(id) > 12 {\n  1182→\t\treturn id[:12]\n  1183→\t}\n  1184→\treturn id\n  1185→}\n  1186→\n  1187→// projectLabels builds a mapping from full project directory paths to short\n  1188→// display labels. Each label is the final directory component (e.g.\n  1189→// \"myproject\" from \"/home/user/workspace/myproject\"). When two projects share\n  1190→// the same final name, the parent directory is prepended to disambiguate\n  1191→// (e.g. \"foo/bar\" vs \"baz/bar\").\n  1192→func projectLabels(dirs []string) map[string]string {\n  1193→\tlabels := make(map[string]string, len(dirs))\n  1194→\t// Group dirs by their base name to detect conflicts.\n  1195→\tbyBase := map[string][]string{}\n  1196→\tfor _, d := range dirs {\n  1197→\t\tbase := filepath.Base(d)\n  1198→\t\tbyBase[base] = append(byBase[base], d)\n  1199→\t}\n  1200→\tfor base, paths := range byBase {\n  1201→\t\tif len(paths) == 1 {\n  1202→\t\t\tlabels[paths[0]] = base\n  1203→\t\t} else {\n  1204→\t\t\tfor _, p := range paths {\n  1205→\t\t\t\tparent := filepath.Base(filepath.Dir(p))\n  1206→\t\t\t\tlabels[p] = parent + \"/\" + base\n  1207→\t\t\t}\n  1208→\t\t}\n  1209→\t}\n  1210→\treturn labels\n  1211→}\n  1212→\n  1213→type projectEntry struct {\n  1214→\tDir            string\n  1215→\tLabel          string\n  1216→\tContainerCount int\n  1217→}\n  1218→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"508569cd-e03d-4249-9b5e-689a8c858cef","uuid":"f43c7566-9b2b-4fec-9c12-46af7b39ac37","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go","content":"package web\n\nimport (\n\t\"bufio\"\n\t\"context\"\n\t\"embed\"\n\t\"encoding/json\"\n\t\"fmt\"\n\t\"html/template\"\n\t\"io/fs\"\n\t\"net/http\"\n\t\"net/url\"\n\t\"os\"\n\t\"os/exec\"\n\t\"path/filepath\"\n\t\"regexp\"\n\t\"sort\"\n\t\"strconv\"\n\t\"strings\"\n\t\"time\"\n\n\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/domain\"\n\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/dsl\"\n\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/logstream\"\n\t\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/ports\"\n)\n\n// HandlerOption configures optional Handler dependencies.\ntype HandlerOption func(*Handler)\n\n// WithContainerLogger sets the container runtime for fetching live logs.\nfunc WithContainerLogger(c ContainerLogger) HandlerOption {\n\treturn func(h *Handler) { h.container = c }\n}\n\n// WithContainerManager sets a full container manager (logs, inspect, remove).\nfunc WithContainerManager(c ContainerManager) HandlerOption {\n\treturn func(h *Handler) { h.container = c }\n}\n\n// WithLogBroadcaster sets the log broadcaster for SSE streaming.\nfunc WithLogBroadcaster(b *logstream.Broadcaster) HandlerOption {\n\treturn func(h *Handler) { h.logBroadcast = b }\n}\n\n// WithLogStore sets the log store for indexed log file lookups.\nfunc WithLogStore(ls ports.LogStore) HandlerOption {\n\treturn func(h *Handler) { h.logStore = ls }\n}\n\n//go:embed templates/*.html static/*\nvar content embed.FS\n\n// Handler serves the web dashboard.\n// ContainerLogger can retrieve logs from a container by ID.\ntype ContainerLogger interface {\n\tLogs(ctx context.Context, containerID string) (string, error)\n}\n\n// ContainerManager extends ContainerLogger with container lifecycle operations.\ntype ContainerManager interface {\n\tContainerLogger\n\tRemove(ctx context.Context, containerID string) error\n\tInspect(ctx context.Context, containerID string) (*ports.ContainerStatus, error)\n}\n\ntype Handler struct {\n\tstore        ports.RunStore\n\tcaptures     ports.CaptureStore\n\tlogStore     ports.LogStore\n\tcontainer    ContainerLogger\n\tlogBroadcast *logstream.Broadcaster\n\tpages        map[string]*template.Template\n\tmux          *http.ServeMux\n}\n\n// NewHandler creates a web dashboard handler.\nfunc NewHandler(store ports.RunStore, captures ports.CaptureStore, opts ...HandlerOption) (*Handler, error) {\n\tfuncMap := template.FuncMap{\n\t\t\"stateColor\":       stateColor,\n\t\t\"healthColor\":      healthColor,\n\t\t\"formatTime\":       formatTime,\n\t\t\"formatDuration\":   formatDuration,\n\t\t\"truncate\":         truncate,\n\t\t\"shortContainerID\": shortContainerID,\n\t}\n\n\tbase, err := template.New(\"\").Funcs(funcMap).ParseFS(content, \"templates/layout.html\")\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"parse layout: %w\", err)\n\t}\n\n\tpages := map[string]*template.Template{}\n\tfor _, page := range []string{\"projects\", \"runs\", \"run_detail\", \"project_detail\"} {\n\t\tclone, err := base.Clone()\n\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"clone layout for %s: %w\", page, err)\n\t\t}\n\t\t_, err = clone.ParseFS(content, \"templates/\"+page+\".html\")\n\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"parse %s: %w\", page, err)\n\t\t}\n\t\tpages[page] = clone\n\t}\n\n\th := &Handler{\n\t\tstore:    store,\n\t\tcaptures: captures,\n\t\tpages:    pages,\n\t\tmux:      http.NewServeMux(),\n\t}\n\tfor _, opt := range opts {\n\t\topt(h)\n\t}\n\n\tstaticFS, err := fs.Sub(content, \"static\")\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"static sub-fs: %w\", err)\n\t}\n\n\th.mux.HandleFunc(\"GET /{$}\", h.handleProjectOverview)\n\th.mux.HandleFunc(\"GET /projects/{name}/runs\", h.handleProjectRuns)\n\th.mux.HandleFunc(\"GET /runs\", h.handleRunsList)\n\th.mux.HandleFunc(\"GET /runs/{id}\", h.handleRunDetail)\n\th.mux.HandleFunc(\"GET /projects/{name}\", h.handleProjectDetail)\n\th.mux.HandleFunc(\"GET /api/projects\", h.handleAPIProjects)\n\th.mux.HandleFunc(\"GET /api/runs\", h.handleAPIRuns)\n\th.mux.HandleFunc(\"GET /api/runs/{id}\", h.handleAPIRunDetail)\n\th.mux.HandleFunc(\"GET /api/runs/{id}/steps/{step}/output\", h.handleAPIStepOutput)\n\th.mux.HandleFunc(\"DELETE /api/runs/{id}/container\", h.handleAPIDeleteContainer)\n\th.mux.HandleFunc(\"GET /api/projects/{name}/info\", h.handleAPIProjectInfo)\n\th.mux.HandleFunc(\"GET /api/projects/{name}/info/prompt-diff\", h.handleAPIPromptDiff)\n\th.mux.HandleFunc(\"GET /api/projects/{name}/workflows\", h.handleAPIWorkflows)\n\th.mux.HandleFunc(\"GET /api/projects/{name}/workflows/{workflow}/steps/{step}/content\", h.handleAPIStepContent)\n\th.mux.HandleFunc(\"GET /api/runs/{id}/stream\", h.handleAPIStream)\n\th.mux.Handle(\"GET /static/\", http.StripPrefix(\"/static/\", http.FileServerFS(staticFS)))\n\n\treturn h, nil\n}\n\nfunc (h *Handler) ServeHTTP(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n\th.mux.ServeHTTP(w, r)\n}\n\n// --- HTML handlers ---\n\n// projectOverviewEntry holds data for a single project card on the landing page.\ntype projectOverviewEntry struct {\n\tDir         string\n\tLabel       string\n\tHealth      domain.HealthResult\n\tRecentRuns  []recentRunDot\n\tActiveCount int\n}\n\n// recentRunDot is a minimal representation of a run for the mini history display.\ntype recentRunDot struct {\n\tID    string\n\tState string\n}\n\nconst healthWindowSize = 10\n\nfunc (h *Handler) handleProjectOverview(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n\tprojects, _ := h.store.ListProjects(r.Context())\n\tlabels := projectLabels(projects)\n\n\tvar entries []projectOverviewEntry\n\tfor _, dir := range projects {\n\t\truns, err := h.store.ListRunsByProject(r.Context(), dir, time.Time{})\n\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t}\n\n\t\t// Convert []*domain.Run to []domain.Run for CalculateHealth.\n\t\trunValues := make([]domain.Run, len(runs))\n\t\tfor i, rr := range runs {\n\t\t\trunValues[i] = *rr\n\t\t}\n\n\t\thealth := domain.CalculateHealth(runValues, healthWindowSize)\n\n\t\t// Take the last N runs for the mini history (most recent first).\n\t\tn := healthWindowSize\n\t\tif n > len(runs) {\n\t\t\tn = len(runs)\n\t\t}\n\t\tdots := make([]recentRunDot, n)\n\t\tfor i := 0; i < n; i++ {\n\t\t\tdots[i] = recentRunDot{\n\t\t\t\tID:    runs[i].ID,\n\t\t\t\tState: string(runs[i].State),\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t}\n\n\t\tvar activeCount int\n\t\tfor _, rr := range runs {\n\t\t\tif rr.State == domain.RunStatePending || rr.State == domain.RunStateRunning {\n\t\t\t\tactiveCount++\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t}\n\n\t\tentries = append(entries, projectOverviewEntry{\n\t\t\tDir:         dir,\n\t\t\tLabel:       labels[dir],\n\t\t\tHealth:      health,\n\t\t\tRecentRuns:  dots,\n\t\t\tActiveCount: activeCount,\n\t\t})\n\t}\n\n\tsort.Slice(entries, func(i, j int) bool {\n\t\treturn entries[i].Label < entries[j].Label\n\t})\n\n\tdata := map[string]any{\n\t\t\"Title\":    \"Projects\",\n\t\t\"Projects\": entries,\n\t}\n\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"text/html; charset=utf-8\")\n\tif err := h.pages[\"projects\"].ExecuteTemplate(w, \"layout\", data); err != nil {\n\t\thttp.Error(w, err.Error(), http.StatusInternalServerError)\n\t}\n}\n\nfunc (h *Handler) handleRunsList(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n\tprojectFilter := r.URL.Query().Get(\"project\")\n\n\tvar runs []*domain.Run\n\tvar err error\n\tif projectFilter != \"\" {\n\t\truns, err = h.store.ListRunsByProject(r.Context(), projectFilter, time.Time{})\n\t} else {\n\t\truns, err = h.store.ListRuns(r.Context(), time.Time{})\n\t}\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\thttp.Error(w, \"failed to list runs\", http.StatusInternalServerError)\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\n\tprojects, _ := h.store.ListProjects(r.Context())\n\tlabels := projectLabels(projects)\n\n\t// Count retained containers per project\n\tcontainerCounts := map[string]int{}\n\tallRuns, _ := h.store.ListRuns(r.Context(), time.Time{})\n\tfor _, run := range allRuns {\n\t\tif run.ContainerKept {\n\t\t\tcontainerCounts[run.ProjectDir]++\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\tvar projectList []projectEntry\n\tfor _, dir := range projects {\n\t\tprojectList = append(projectList, projectEntry{Dir: dir, Label: labels[dir], ContainerCount: containerCounts[dir]})\n\t}\n\tsort.Slice(projectList, func(i, j int) bool {\n\t\treturn projectList[i].Label < projectList[j].Label\n\t})\n\n\tdata := map[string]any{\n\t\t\"Title\":         \"Runs\",\n\t\t\"Runs\":          runs,\n\t\t\"Projects\":      projectList,\n\t\t\"ProjectFilter\": projectFilter,\n\t\t\"ProjectLabels\": labels,\n\t}\n\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"text/html; charset=utf-8\")\n\tif err := h.pages[\"runs\"].ExecuteTemplate(w, \"layout\", data); err != nil {\n\t\thttp.Error(w, err.Error(), http.StatusInternalServerError)\n\t}\n}\n\n// handleProjectRuns redirects /projects/{name}/runs to /runs?project=<dir>.\nfunc (h *Handler) handleProjectRuns(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n\tdir, _, ok := h.resolveProjectDir(w, r)\n\tif !ok {\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\thttp.Redirect(w, r, \"/runs?project=\"+url.QueryEscape(dir), http.StatusFound)\n}\n\n// stepEntry is a merged view of a step execution for the template.\ntype stepEntry struct {\n\tIndex     int\n\tStepName  string\n\tResult    string\n\tStartedAt time.Time\n\tDuration  string\n}\n\n// mergeCaptures collapses started/completed capture pairs into single entries.\nfunc mergeCaptures(caps []*domain.StepExecution) []stepEntry {\n\tvar entries []stepEntry\n\t// Track pending started rows by step name (LIFO for retries)\n\tpending := map[string]*domain.StepExecution{}\n\n\tfor _, c := range caps {\n\t\tif c.Result == \"\" {\n\t\t\t// step_started row\n\t\t\tpending[c.StepName] = c\n\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t}\n\t\t// step_completed row — merge with pending started if available\n\t\tstartedAt := c.StartedAt\n\t\tif started := pending[c.StepName]; started != nil {\n\t\t\tstartedAt = started.StartedAt\n\t\t\tdelete(pending, c.StepName)\n\t\t}\n\t\tentries = append(entries, stepEntry{\n\t\t\tIndex:     len(entries),\n\t\t\tStepName:  c.StepName,\n\t\t\tResult:    c.Result,\n\t\t\tStartedAt: startedAt,\n\t\t\tDuration:  formatDuration(startedAt, c.CompletedAt),\n\t\t})\n\t}\n\n\t// Append any started-but-not-completed steps (still running)\n\tfor _, c := range caps {\n\t\tif c.Result == \"\" {\n\t\t\tif _, used := pending[c.StepName]; !used {\n\t\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\tentries = append(entries, stepEntry{\n\t\t\t\tIndex:     len(entries),\n\t\t\t\tStepName:  c.StepName,\n\t\t\t\tStartedAt: c.StartedAt,\n\t\t\t})\n\t\t\tdelete(pending, c.StepName)\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\treturn entries\n}\n\n// containerState inspects the container for a run and returns one of:\n//   - \"running\"   – container exists and is running\n//   - \"stopped\"   – container exists, not running, not kept\n//   - \"available\" – container exists, not running, kept (can be deleted)\n//   - \"removed\"   – no container ID, no manager, or inspect failed\nfunc (h *Handler) containerState(ctx context.Context, run *domain.Run) string {\n\tif run.ContainerID == \"\" {\n\t\treturn \"removed\"\n\t}\n\tmgr, ok := h.container.(ContainerManager)\n\tif !ok {\n\t\treturn \"removed\"\n\t}\n\tstatus, err := mgr.Inspect(ctx, run.ContainerID)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn \"removed\"\n\t}\n\tif status.Running {\n\t\treturn \"running\"\n\t}\n\tif run.ContainerKept {\n\t\treturn \"available\"\n\t}\n\treturn \"stopped\"\n}\n\nfunc (h *Handler) handleRunDetail(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n\tid := r.PathValue(\"id\")\n\n\trun, err := h.store.GetRun(r.Context(), id)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\thttp.Error(w, \"run not found\", http.StatusNotFound)\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\n\tcaps, err := h.captures.GetCaptures(r.Context(), id)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\tcaps = nil // non-fatal\n\t}\n\n\tsteps := mergeCaptures(caps)\n\n\tdata := map[string]any{\n\t\t\"Title\":          \"Run \" + run.ID,\n\t\t\"Run\":            run,\n\t\t\"Steps\":          steps,\n\t\t\"Page\":           \"detail\",\n\t\t\"ContainerState\": h.containerState(r.Context(), run),\n\t}\n\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"text/html; charset=utf-8\")\n\tif err := h.pages[\"run_detail\"].ExecuteTemplate(w, \"layout\", data); err != nil {\n\t\thttp.Error(w, err.Error(), http.StatusInternalServerError)\n\t}\n}\n\n// --- JSON API handlers ---\n\ntype apiRun struct {\n\tID           string `json:\"id\"`\n\tWorkflowName string `json:\"workflow_name\"`\n\tProjectDir   string `json:\"project_dir\"`\n\tProjectLabel string `json:\"project_label\"`\n\tState        string `json:\"state\"`\n\tStartedAt    string `json:\"started_at\"`\n\tCompletedAt  string `json:\"completed_at\"`\n\tContainerID  string `json:\"container_id\"`\n\tErrorMessage string `json:\"error_message\"`\n\tTitle        string `json:\"title\"`\n\tIsHost       bool   `json:\"is_host\"`\n}\n\ntype apiStep struct {\n\tStepName    string `json:\"step_name\"`\n\tResult      string `json:\"result\"`\n\tStartedAt   string `json:\"started_at\"`\n\tCompletedAt string `json:\"completed_at\"`\n\tDuration    string `json:\"duration\"`\n}\n\ntype apiRunDetail struct {\n\tapiRun\n\tContainerState string    `json:\"container_state\"`\n\tSteps          []apiStep `json:\"steps\"`\n}\n\nfunc toAPIRun(r *domain.Run, labels map[string]string) apiRun {\n\treturn apiRun{\n\t\tID:           r.ID,\n\t\tWorkflowName: r.WorkflowName,\n\t\tProjectDir:   r.ProjectDir,\n\t\tProjectLabel: labels[r.ProjectDir],\n\t\tState:        string(r.State),\n\t\tStartedAt:    formatTime(r.StartedAt),\n\t\tCompletedAt:  formatTime(r.CompletedAt),\n\t\tContainerID:  r.ContainerID,\n\t\tErrorMessage: r.ErrorMessage,\n\t\tTitle:        r.Title,\n\t\tIsHost:       r.IsHost,\n\t}\n}\n\nfunc (h *Handler) handleAPIRuns(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n\tprojectFilter := r.URL.Query().Get(\"project\")\n\n\tvar runs []*domain.Run\n\tvar err error\n\tif projectFilter != \"\" {\n\t\truns, err = h.store.ListRunsByProject(r.Context(), projectFilter, time.Time{})\n\t} else {\n\t\truns, err = h.store.ListRuns(r.Context(), time.Time{})\n\t}\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\thttp.Error(w, \"failed to list runs\", http.StatusInternalServerError)\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\n\tprojects, _ := h.store.ListProjects(r.Context())\n\tlabels := projectLabels(projects)\n\n\tresult := make([]apiRun, len(runs))\n\tfor i, run := range runs {\n\t\tresult[i] = toAPIRun(run, labels)\n\t}\n\n\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n\tjson.NewEncoder(w).Encode(result)\n}\n\nfunc (h *Handler) handleAPIProjects(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n\tprojects, err := h.store.ListProjects(r.Context())\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\thttp.Error(w, \"failed to list projects\", http.StatusInternalServerError)\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\tlabels := projectLabels(projects)\n\n\ttype apiHealth struct {\n\t\tStatus string `json:\"status\"`\n\t\tPassed int    `json:\"passed\"`\n\t\tFailed int    `json:\"failed\"`\n\t\tTotal  int    `json:\"total\"`\n\t}\n\ttype apiProject struct {\n\t\tDir         string    `json:\"dir\"`\n\t\tLabel       string    `json:\"label\"`\n\t\tHealth      apiHealth `json:\"health\"`\n\t\tActiveCount int       `json:\"active_count\"`\n\t}\n\tresult := make([]apiProject, len(projects))\n\tfor i, dir := range projects {\n\t\truns, _ := h.store.ListRunsByProject(r.Context(), dir, time.Time{})\n\t\trunValues := make([]domain.Run, len(runs))\n\t\tfor j, rr := range runs {\n\t\t\trunValues[j] = *rr\n\t\t}\n\t\thealth := domain.CalculateHealth(runValues, healthWindowSize)\n\t\tvar activeCount int\n\t\tfor _, rr := range runs {\n\t\t\tif rr.State == domain.RunStatePending || rr.State == domain.RunStateRunning {\n\t\t\t\tactiveCount++\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t}\n\t\tresult[i] = apiProject{\n\t\t\tDir:   dir,\n\t\t\tLabel: labels[dir],\n\t\t\tHealth: apiHealth{\n\t\t\t\tStatus: string(health.Status),\n\t\t\t\tPassed: health.Passed,\n\t\t\t\tFailed: health.Failed,\n\t\t\t\tTotal:  health.Total,\n\t\t\t},\n\t\t\tActiveCount: activeCount,\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n\tjson.NewEncoder(w).Encode(result)\n}\n\nfunc (h *Handler) handleAPIRunDetail(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n\tid := r.PathValue(\"id\")\n\n\trun, err := h.store.GetRun(r.Context(), id)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\thttp.Error(w, \"run not found\", http.StatusNotFound)\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\n\tcaps, err := h.captures.GetCaptures(r.Context(), id)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\tcaps = nil\n\t}\n\n\tprojects, _ := h.store.ListProjects(r.Context())\n\tlabels := projectLabels(projects)\n\n\tmerged := mergeCaptures(caps)\n\tsteps := make([]apiStep, len(merged))\n\tfor i, e := range merged {\n\t\tsteps[i] = apiStep{\n\t\t\tStepName:  e.StepName,\n\t\t\tResult:    e.Result,\n\t\t\tStartedAt: formatTime(e.StartedAt),\n\t\t\tDuration:  e.Duration,\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\tdetail := apiRunDetail{\n\t\tapiRun:         toAPIRun(run, labels),\n\t\tContainerState: h.containerState(r.Context(), run),\n\t\tSteps:          steps,\n\t}\n\n\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n\tjson.NewEncoder(w).Encode(detail)\n}\n\nfunc (h *Handler) handleAPIStepOutput(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n\tid := r.PathValue(\"id\")\n\tstep := r.PathValue(\"step\")\n\tlogType := r.URL.Query().Get(\"type\")   // optional: \"script\", \"llm\"\n\tformat := r.URL.Query().Get(\"format\")  // optional: \"raw\" to skip parsing\n\n\trun, err := h.store.GetRun(r.Context(), id)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\thttp.Error(w, \"run not found\", http.StatusNotFound)\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\n\twriteOutput := func(data []byte) {\n\t\tif format != \"raw\" {\n\t\t\tdata = logstream.ParseClaudeStream(data)\n\t\t}\n\t\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"text/plain; charset=utf-8\")\n\t\tw.Write(data)\n\t}\n\n\t// Try log index first for fast lookup\n\tif h.logStore != nil {\n\t\tlogFiles, err := h.logStore.GetLogFilesByStep(r.Context(), id, step)\n\t\tif err == nil && len(logFiles) > 0 {\n\t\t\t// If type filter specified, narrow results\n\t\t\tfor _, lf := range logFiles {\n\t\t\t\tif logType != \"\" && lf.FileType != logType {\n\t\t\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t\tdata, readErr := os.ReadFile(lf.FilePath)\n\t\t\t\tif readErr == nil && len(data) > 0 {\n\t\t\t\t\twriteOutput(data)\n\t\t\t\t\treturn\n\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\toutputDir := filepath.Join(run.ProjectDir, \".cloche\", id, \"output\")\n\n\t// Fall back to file path conventions\n\t// If type is \"llm\", try llm-<step>.log\n\tif logType == \"llm\" {\n\t\tllmPath := filepath.Join(outputDir, \"llm-\"+step+\".log\")\n\t\tdata, err := os.ReadFile(llmPath)\n\t\tif err == nil && len(data) > 0 {\n\t\t\twriteOutput(data)\n\t\t\treturn\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\t// Try per-step output first, fall back to container.log, then live docker logs\n\toutputPath := filepath.Join(outputDir, step+\".log\")\n\tdata, err := os.ReadFile(outputPath)\n\tif err == nil && len(data) > 0 {\n\t\twriteOutput(data)\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\n\tcontainerLog := filepath.Join(outputDir, \"container.log\")\n\tdata, err = os.ReadFile(containerLog)\n\tif err == nil && len(data) > 0 {\n\t\twriteOutput(data)\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\n\t// Last resort: try live docker logs from still-existing container\n\tif h.container != nil && run.ContainerID != \"\" {\n\t\tif logs, logErr := h.container.Logs(r.Context(), run.ContainerID); logErr == nil && logs != \"\" {\n\t\t\twriteOutput([]byte(logs))\n\t\t\treturn\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\thttp.Error(w, \"step output not found\", http.StatusNotFound)\n}\n\nfunc (h *Handler) handleAPIDeleteContainer(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n\tid := r.PathValue(\"id\")\n\n\trun, err := h.store.GetRun(r.Context(), id)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n\t\tw.WriteHeader(http.StatusNotFound)\n\t\tjson.NewEncoder(w).Encode(map[string]string{\"error\": \"run not found\"})\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\n\tmgr, ok := h.container.(ContainerManager)\n\tif !ok || run.ContainerID == \"\" {\n\t\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n\t\tw.WriteHeader(http.StatusBadRequest)\n\t\tjson.NewEncoder(w).Encode(map[string]string{\"error\": \"container management not available\"})\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\n\tif err := mgr.Remove(r.Context(), run.ContainerID); err != nil {\n\t\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n\t\tw.WriteHeader(http.StatusInternalServerError)\n\t\tjson.NewEncoder(w).Encode(map[string]string{\"error\": fmt.Sprintf(\"failed to remove container: %v\", err)})\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\n\trun.ContainerKept = false\n\tif err := h.store.UpdateRun(r.Context(), run); err != nil {\n\t\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n\t\tw.WriteHeader(http.StatusInternalServerError)\n\t\tjson.NewEncoder(w).Encode(map[string]string{\"error\": fmt.Sprintf(\"failed to update run: %v\", err)})\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\n\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n\tjson.NewEncoder(w).Encode(map[string]string{\"status\": \"ok\"})\n}\n\n// handleAPIStream serves an SSE stream of log lines for a run.\n// For active runs, it subscribes to the live broadcaster.\n// For completed runs, it serves the archived full.log then closes.\nfunc (h *Handler) handleAPIStream(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n\tid := r.PathValue(\"id\")\n\n\trun, err := h.store.GetRun(r.Context(), id)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\thttp.Error(w, \"run not found\", http.StatusNotFound)\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\n\tflusher, ok := w.(http.Flusher)\n\tif !ok {\n\t\thttp.Error(w, \"streaming not supported\", http.StatusInternalServerError)\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\n\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"text/event-stream\")\n\tw.Header().Set(\"Cache-Control\", \"no-cache\")\n\tw.Header().Set(\"Connection\", \"keep-alive\")\n\tw.Header().Set(\"X-Accel-Buffering\", \"no\")\n\n\tisComplete := run.State == domain.RunStateSucceeded ||\n\t\trun.State == domain.RunStateFailed ||\n\t\trun.State == domain.RunStateCancelled\n\n\tif isComplete {\n\t\t// Serve archived full.log\n\t\th.streamFullLog(w, flusher, run)\n\t\t// Send done event\n\t\tfmt.Fprintf(w, \"event: done\\ndata: %s\\n\\n\", string(run.State))\n\t\tflusher.Flush()\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\n\t// Active run: subscribe to live broadcaster\n\tif h.logBroadcast == nil {\n\t\thttp.Error(w, \"log streaming not available\", http.StatusServiceUnavailable)\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\n\tsub := h.logBroadcast.Subscribe(id)\n\tdefer h.logBroadcast.Unsubscribe(id, sub)\n\n\tctx := r.Context()\n\tfor {\n\t\tselect {\n\t\tcase <-ctx.Done():\n\t\t\treturn\n\t\tcase line, ok := <-sub.C:\n\t\t\tif !ok {\n\t\t\t\t// Stream finished (run completed)\n\t\t\t\tfmt.Fprintf(w, \"event: done\\ndata: completed\\n\\n\")\n\t\t\t\tflusher.Flush()\n\t\t\t\treturn\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\tline = parseLLMLogLine(line)\n\t\t\tif line.Type == \"\" {\n\t\t\t\tcontinue // skip protocol-only llm lines\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\tdata, _ := json.Marshal(line)\n\t\t\tfmt.Fprintf(w, \"data: %s\\n\\n\", data)\n\t\t\tflusher.Flush()\n\t\t}\n\t}\n}\n\n// logLineRegex parses \"[timestamp] [type] content\" format from full.log.\nvar logLineRegex = regexp.MustCompile(`^\\[([^\\]]+)\\] \\[([^\\]]+)\\] (.*)$`)\n\n// streamFullLog reads the archived full.log file and sends its entries as SSE events.\n// LLM-type lines are parsed from raw Claude JSON into human-readable text.\nfunc (h *Handler) streamFullLog(w http.ResponseWriter, flusher http.Flusher, run *domain.Run) {\n\tlogPath := filepath.Join(run.ProjectDir, \".cloche\", run.ID, \"output\", \"full.log\")\n\tf, err := os.Open(logPath)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\tdefer f.Close()\n\n\tscanner := bufio.NewScanner(f)\n\tfor scanner.Scan() {\n\t\ttext := scanner.Text()\n\t\tline := parseFullLogLine(text)\n\t\tline = parseLLMLogLine(line)\n\t\tif line.Type == \"\" {\n\t\t\tcontinue // skip protocol-only llm lines\n\t\t}\n\t\tdata, _ := json.Marshal(line)\n\t\tfmt.Fprintf(w, \"data: %s\\n\\n\", data)\n\t\tflusher.Flush()\n\t}\n}\n\n// parseLLMLogLine parses a LogLine whose type is \"llm\". If the content is\n// Claude stream JSON, it extracts the human-readable text. Protocol-only\n// events return a LogLine with an empty Type (caller should skip it).\n// Non-llm lines are returned unchanged.\nfunc parseLLMLogLine(line logstream.LogLine) logstream.LogLine {\n\tif line.Type != \"llm\" {\n\t\treturn line\n\t}\n\ttext, ok := logstream.ParseClaudeLine([]byte(line.Content))\n\tif !ok {\n\t\treturn logstream.LogLine{} // signal to skip\n\t}\n\tline.Content = text\n\treturn line\n}\n\n// parseFullLogLine parses a \"[timestamp] [type] content\" line into a LogLine.\nfunc parseFullLogLine(text string) logstream.LogLine {\n\tm := logLineRegex.FindStringSubmatch(text)\n\tif m == nil {\n\t\treturn logstream.LogLine{\n\t\t\tTimestamp: time.Now().UTC().Format(time.RFC3339),\n\t\t\tType:      \"script\",\n\t\t\tContent:   text,\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\treturn logstream.LogLine{\n\t\tTimestamp: m[1],\n\t\tType:      m[2],\n\t\tContent:   m[3],\n\t}\n}\n\n// --- Project detail handlers ---\n\n// resolveProjectDir resolves a project label from the URL to its directory path.\n// Returns (dir, label, ok). Writes a JSON error response if not found.\nfunc (h *Handler) resolveProjectDir(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) (string, string, bool) {\n\tlabel := r.PathValue(\"name\")\n\tprojects, _ := h.store.ListProjects(r.Context())\n\tlabels := projectLabels(projects)\n\tfor dir, l := range labels {\n\t\tif l == label {\n\t\t\treturn dir, label, true\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n\tw.WriteHeader(http.StatusNotFound)\n\tjson.NewEncoder(w).Encode(map[string]string{\"error\": \"project not found\"})\n\treturn \"\", \"\", false\n}\n\nfunc (h *Handler) handleProjectDetail(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n\tdir, label, ok := h.resolveProjectDir(w, r)\n\tif !ok {\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\n\truns, _ := h.store.ListRunsByProject(r.Context(), dir, time.Time{})\n\tn := 10\n\tif n > len(runs) {\n\t\tn = len(runs)\n\t}\n\tdots := make([]recentRunDot, n)\n\tfor i := 0; i < n; i++ {\n\t\tdots[i] = recentRunDot{ID: runs[i].ID, State: string(runs[i].State)}\n\t}\n\n\tdata := map[string]any{\n\t\t\"Title\":      label,\n\t\t\"Label\":      label,\n\t\t\"Dir\":        dir,\n\t\t\"RecentRuns\": dots,\n\t}\n\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"text/html; charset=utf-8\")\n\tif err := h.pages[\"project_detail\"].ExecuteTemplate(w, \"layout\", data); err != nil {\n\t\thttp.Error(w, err.Error(), http.StatusInternalServerError)\n\t}\n}\n\nfunc (h *Handler) handleAPIProjectInfo(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n\tdir, _, ok := h.resolveProjectDir(w, r)\n\tif !ok {\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\n\t// Docker image: read FROM line from Dockerfile\n\tdockerImage := \"\"\n\tdockerfilePath := filepath.Join(dir, \".cloche\", \"Dockerfile\")\n\tif data, err := os.ReadFile(dockerfilePath); err == nil {\n\t\t// Find the last FROM line (final stage)\n\t\tfor _, line := range strings.Split(string(data), \"\\n\") {\n\t\t\ttrimmed := strings.TrimSpace(line)\n\t\t\tif strings.HasPrefix(strings.ToUpper(trimmed), \"FROM \") {\n\t\t\t\tparts := strings.Fields(trimmed)\n\t\t\t\tif len(parts) >= 2 {\n\t\t\t\t\tdockerImage = parts[1]\n\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\t// Version\n\tversion := 0\n\tversionPath := filepath.Join(dir, \".cloche\", \"version\")\n\tif data, err := os.ReadFile(versionPath); err == nil {\n\t\tif v, err := strconv.Atoi(strings.TrimSpace(string(data))); err == nil {\n\t\t\tversion = v\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\t// Prompt files history\n\ttype commitEntry struct {\n\t\tSHA     string `json:\"sha\"`\n\t\tDate    string `json:\"date\"`\n\t\tMessage string `json:\"message\"`\n\t}\n\ttype promptFile struct {\n\t\tPath    string        `json:\"path\"`\n\t\tHistory []commitEntry `json:\"history\"`\n\t}\n\n\tvar promptFiles []promptFile\n\tpromptsDir := filepath.Join(dir, \".cloche\", \"prompts\")\n\tif entries, err := os.ReadDir(promptsDir); err == nil {\n\t\tfor _, e := range entries {\n\t\t\tif e.IsDir() {\n\t\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\trelPath := filepath.Join(\".cloche\", \"prompts\", e.Name())\n\t\t\tcmd := exec.Command(\"git\", \"log\", \"--follow\", \"--format=%H %aI %s\", \"--\", relPath)\n\t\t\tcmd.Dir = dir\n\t\t\tout, err := cmd.Output()\n\t\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\tvar history []commitEntry\n\t\t\tfor _, line := range strings.Split(strings.TrimSpace(string(out)), \"\\n\") {\n\t\t\t\tif line == \"\" {\n\t\t\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t\tparts := strings.SplitN(line, \" \", 3)\n\t\t\t\tif len(parts) < 3 {\n\t\t\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t\t// Parse date to short form\n\t\t\t\tdateStr := parts[1]\n\t\t\t\tif t, err := time.Parse(time.RFC3339, dateStr); err == nil {\n\t\t\t\t\tdateStr = t.Format(\"2006-01-02\")\n\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t\thistory = append(history, commitEntry{\n\t\t\t\t\tSHA:     parts[0][:7],\n\t\t\t\t\tDate:    dateStr,\n\t\t\t\t\tMessage: parts[2],\n\t\t\t\t})\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\tpromptFiles = append(promptFiles, promptFile{Path: relPath, History: history})\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n\tjson.NewEncoder(w).Encode(map[string]any{\n\t\t\"docker_image\": dockerImage,\n\t\t\"version\":      version,\n\t\t\"prompt_files\": promptFiles,\n\t})\n}\n\nfunc (h *Handler) handleAPIPromptDiff(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n\tdir, _, ok := h.resolveProjectDir(w, r)\n\tif !ok {\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\tfile := r.URL.Query().Get(\"file\")\n\tsha := r.URL.Query().Get(\"sha\")\n\tif file == \"\" || sha == \"\" {\n\t\thttp.Error(w, \"file and sha required\", http.StatusBadRequest)\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\n\t// Validate sha is alphanumeric to prevent injection\n\tfor _, c := range sha {\n\t\tif !((c >= '0' && c <= '9') || (c >= 'a' && c <= 'f') || (c >= 'A' && c <= 'F')) {\n\t\t\thttp.Error(w, \"invalid sha\", http.StatusBadRequest)\n\t\t\treturn\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\tcmd := exec.Command(\"git\", \"diff\", sha+\"^..\"+sha, \"--\", file)\n\tcmd.Dir = dir\n\tout, err := cmd.Output()\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\thttp.Error(w, \"diff not available\", http.StatusNotFound)\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"text/plain; charset=utf-8\")\n\tw.Write(out)\n}\n\nfunc (h *Handler) handleAPIWorkflows(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n\tdir, _, ok := h.resolveProjectDir(w, r)\n\tif !ok {\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\n\tclocheDir := filepath.Join(dir, \".cloche\")\n\tentries, err := os.ReadDir(clocheDir)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n\t\tjson.NewEncoder(w).Encode([]any{})\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\n\ttype apiWire struct {\n\t\tFrom   string `json:\"from\"`\n\t\tResult string `json:\"result\"`\n\t\tTo     string `json:\"to\"`\n\t}\n\ttype apiStepDef struct {\n\t\tName    string            `json:\"name\"`\n\t\tType    string            `json:\"type\"`\n\t\tResults []string          `json:\"results\"`\n\t\tConfig  map[string]string `json:\"config\"`\n\t}\n\ttype apiWorkflow struct {\n\t\tName      string       `json:\"name\"`\n\t\tFile      string       `json:\"file\"`\n\t\tSteps     []apiStepDef `json:\"steps\"`\n\t\tWires     []apiWire    `json:\"wires\"`\n\t\tEntryStep string       `json:\"entry_step\"`\n\t}\n\n\tvar workflows []apiWorkflow\n\tfor _, e := range entries {\n\t\tif e.IsDir() || !strings.HasSuffix(e.Name(), \".cloche\") || e.Name() == \"host.cloche\" {\n\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t}\n\t\tdata, err := os.ReadFile(filepath.Join(clocheDir, e.Name()))\n\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t}\n\t\twf, err := dsl.ParseForContainer(string(data))\n\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t}\n\t\tvar steps []apiStepDef\n\t\tfor _, s := range wf.Steps {\n\t\t\tsteps = append(steps, apiStepDef{\n\t\t\t\tName:    s.Name,\n\t\t\t\tType:    string(s.Type),\n\t\t\t\tResults: s.Results,\n\t\t\t\tConfig:  s.Config,\n\t\t\t})\n\t\t}\n\t\t// Sort steps by name for consistent ordering\n\t\tsort.Slice(steps, func(i, j int) bool { return steps[i].Name < steps[j].Name })\n\n\t\tvar wires []apiWire\n\t\tfor _, wire := range wf.Wiring {\n\t\t\twires = append(wires, apiWire{From: wire.From, Result: wire.Result, To: wire.To})\n\t\t}\n\n\t\tworkflows = append(workflows, apiWorkflow{\n\t\t\tName:      wf.Name,\n\t\t\tFile:      filepath.Join(\".cloche\", e.Name()),\n\t\t\tSteps:     steps,\n\t\t\tWires:     wires,\n\t\t\tEntryStep: wf.EntryStep,\n\t\t})\n\t}\n\n\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"application/json\")\n\tjson.NewEncoder(w).Encode(workflows)\n}\n\nfunc (h *Handler) handleAPIStepContent(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n\tdir, _, ok := h.resolveProjectDir(w, r)\n\tif !ok {\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\tworkflowName := r.PathValue(\"workflow\")\n\tstepName := r.PathValue(\"step\")\n\n\t// Find the workflow file\n\tclocheDir := filepath.Join(dir, \".cloche\")\n\tvar wf *domain.Workflow\n\tentries, _ := os.ReadDir(clocheDir)\n\tfor _, e := range entries {\n\t\tif e.IsDir() || !strings.HasSuffix(e.Name(), \".cloche\") || e.Name() == \"host.cloche\" {\n\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t}\n\t\tdata, err := os.ReadFile(filepath.Join(clocheDir, e.Name()))\n\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t}\n\t\tparsed, err := dsl.ParseForContainer(string(data))\n\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t}\n\t\tif parsed.Name == workflowName {\n\t\t\twf = parsed\n\t\t\tbreak\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\tif wf == nil {\n\t\thttp.Error(w, \"workflow not found\", http.StatusNotFound)\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\n\tstep, ok := wf.Steps[stepName]\n\tif !ok {\n\t\thttp.Error(w, \"step not found\", http.StatusNotFound)\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\n\t// Try to read the referenced file from step config\n\tw.Header().Set(\"Content-Type\", \"text/plain; charset=utf-8\")\n\n\tif prompt := step.Config[\"prompt\"]; prompt != \"\" {\n\t\tcontent, err := resolveFileRef(prompt, dir)\n\t\tif err == nil {\n\t\t\tw.Write([]byte(content))\n\t\t\treturn\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\tif cmd := step.Config[\"command\"]; cmd != \"\" {\n\t\tcontent, _ := resolveFileRef(cmd, dir)\n\t\tw.Write([]byte(content))\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\tif script := step.Config[\"script\"]; script != \"\" {\n\t\tcontent, _ := resolveFileRef(script, dir)\n\t\tw.Write([]byte(content))\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\n\thttp.Error(w, \"no content available\", http.StatusNotFound)\n}\n\n// --- Template helpers ---\n\n// resolveFileRef resolves file(\"path\") DSL syntax to actual file contents.\n// If the value uses file() syntax, the referenced file is read from disk.\n// Otherwise the value is returned as-is.\nfunc resolveFileRef(value, baseDir string) (string, error) {\n\tif strings.HasPrefix(value, `file(\"`) && strings.HasSuffix(value, `\")`) {\n\t\tpath := value[6 : len(value)-2]\n\t\tdata, err := os.ReadFile(filepath.Join(baseDir, path))\n\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\treturn \"\", err\n\t\t}\n\t\treturn string(data), nil\n\t}\n\treturn value, nil\n}\n\nfunc stateColor(state domain.RunState) string {\n\tswitch state {\n\tcase domain.RunStatePending:\n\t\treturn \"pending\"\n\tcase domain.RunStateRunning:\n\t\treturn \"running\"\n\tcase domain.RunStateSucceeded:\n\t\treturn \"succeeded\"\n\tcase domain.RunStateFailed:\n\t\treturn \"failed\"\n\tcase domain.RunStateCancelled:\n\t\treturn \"cancelled\"\n\tdefault:\n\t\treturn \"pending\"\n\t}\n}\n\nfunc healthColor(status domain.HealthStatus) string {\n\tswitch status {\n\tcase domain.HealthGreen:\n\t\treturn \"green\"\n\tcase domain.HealthYellow:\n\t\treturn \"yellow\"\n\tcase domain.HealthRed:\n\t\treturn \"red\"\n\tcase domain.HealthBlue:\n\t\treturn \"blue\"\n\tdefault:\n\t\treturn \"grey\"\n\t}\n}\n\nfunc formatTime(t time.Time) string {\n\tif t.IsZero() {\n\t\treturn \"\"\n\t}\n\treturn t.Format(\"2006-01-02 15:04:05\")\n}\n\nfunc formatDuration(start, end time.Time) string {\n\tif start.IsZero() || end.IsZero() {\n\t\treturn \"\"\n\t}\n\td := end.Sub(start)\n\tif d < time.Second {\n\t\treturn fmt.Sprintf(\"%dms\", d.Milliseconds())\n\t}\n\tif d < time.Minute {\n\t\treturn fmt.Sprintf(\"%.1fs\", d.Seconds())\n\t}\n\treturn fmt.Sprintf(\"%dm%ds\", int(d.Minutes()), int(d.Seconds())%60)\n}\n\nfunc truncate(s string, n int) string {\n\tif len(s) <= n {\n\t\treturn s\n\t}\n\treturn s[:n] + \"...\"\n}\n\nfunc shortContainerID(id string) string {\n\tif len(id) > 12 {\n\t\treturn id[:12]\n\t}\n\treturn id\n}\n\n// projectLabels builds a mapping from full project directory paths to short\n// display labels. Each label is the final directory component (e.g.\n// \"myproject\" from \"/home/user/workspace/myproject\"). When two projects share\n// the same final name, the parent directory is prepended to disambiguate\n// (e.g. \"foo/bar\" vs \"baz/bar\").\nfunc projectLabels(dirs []string) map[string]string {\n\tlabels := make(map[string]string, len(dirs))\n\t// Group dirs by their base name to detect conflicts.\n\tbyBase := map[string][]string{}\n\tfor _, d := range dirs {\n\t\tbase := filepath.Base(d)\n\t\tbyBase[base] = append(byBase[base], d)\n\t}\n\tfor base, paths := range byBase {\n\t\tif len(paths) == 1 {\n\t\t\tlabels[paths[0]] = base\n\t\t} else {\n\t\t\tfor _, p := range paths {\n\t\t\t\tparent := filepath.Base(filepath.Dir(p))\n\t\t\t\tlabels[p] = parent + \"/\" + base\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\treturn labels\n}\n\ntype projectEntry struct {\n\tDir            string\n\tLabel          string\n\tContainerCount int\n}\n","numLines":1218,"startLine":1,"totalLines":1218}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01FZTQy6D6nmZXX9reUbH6Xv","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to understand how the web handler can stop a run. The gRPC server has a `StopRun` method, but the web handler doesn't have access to it directly. I need to add:\n\n1. A `RunStopper` interface to the web handler\n2. A `POST /api/runs/{id}/stop` endpoint\n3. A Cancel button in the template\n4. JavaScript to call the endpoint\n\nLet me check how the ContainerManager is wired up to understand the pattern for adding a new interface.\n\nThe web handler needs a way to stop runs. Looking at the gRPC server's `StopRun`, it:\n\n\n- Looks up the container ID from the `runIDs` map\n- Calls `container.Stop()` on the container runtime\n- Marks the run as cancelled\n\nThe web handler already has a `ContainerManager` interface, but the actual stop logic lives on the `ContainerRuntime` interface, so I need to figure out how to wire that dependency into the web handler.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":20569,"cache_read_input_tokens":17011,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":20569},"output_tokens":9,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"508569cd-e03d-4249-9b5e-689a8c858cef","uuid":"68df0dde-d3fa-42c9-8b0c-e70ea4afa7d5"}
